WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:26.693 --> 00:00:28.695
♪ ♪

3
00:00:42.751 --> 00:00:44.795
(crowd clamoring)

4
00:00:47.047 --> 00:00:50.967
- (boot thumping)
- CROWD: One! Two! Three!

5
00:00:50.968 --> 00:00:52.760
(laughs menacingly)

6
00:00:52.761 --> 00:00:54.512
Yeah!

7
00:00:54.513 --> 00:00:56.222
(yells)

8
00:00:56.223 --> 00:00:58.182
(yells. grunts)

9
00:00:58.183 --> 00:01:00.226
(cheering)

10
00:01:00.227 --> 00:01:01.812
Come on! Yeah!

11
00:01:04.481 --> 00:01:05.523
Come on!

12
00:01:05.524 --> 00:01:07.191
(yells)

13
00:01:07.192 --> 00:01:09.820
- (laughs)
- (crowd shouting)

14
00:01:14.157 --> 00:01:15.908
Let's do this! Come on!

15
00:01:15.909 --> 00:01:17.618
Come on!

16
00:01:17.619 --> 00:01:20.205
(yells. grunts)

17
00:01:21.123 --> 00:01:23.666
Come on! Come on!

18
00:01:23.667 --> 00:01:25.084
(chair clatters)

19
00:01:25.085 --> 00:01:26.919
(grunts) Come on.

20
00:01:26.920 --> 00:01:28.296
Let's do this. Come on.

21
00:01:28.297 --> 00:01:29.964
(crowd shouting)

22
00:01:29.965 --> 00:01:32.384
(wrestlers grunting)

23
00:01:36.763 --> 00:01:40.350
MAN: Let the backpack slip off
next time everyone stands.

24
00:01:46.606 --> 00:01:48.483
(cheering)

25
00:01:54.406 --> 00:01:55.781
Where's Jane?

26
00:01:55.782 --> 00:01:57.450
Daniel Kellner.

27
00:01:57.451 --> 00:01:59.828
Do you want to see her again
or not?

28
00:02:03.832 --> 00:02:06.626
(crowd cheering)

29
00:02:10.881 --> 00:02:12.298
Relax.

30
00:02:12.299 --> 00:02:13.674
Enjoy the match.

31
00:02:13.675 --> 00:02:16.135
Just got to make sure
it's all there.

32
00:02:16.136 --> 00:02:18.347
(crowd cheering)

33
00:02:20.307 --> 00:02:24.185
MAN 2:
7.23.48.83

34
00:02:24.186 --> 00:02:28.939
through 3.14.84A.

35
00:02:28.940 --> 00:02:30.483
11.17.55...

36
00:02:30.484 --> 00:02:34.945
I make a total of 107
IronClad drives. 128 gig each.

37
00:02:34.946 --> 00:02:38.282
- You want me to do a recount?
- Uh. when we finish. yes.

38
00:02:38.283 --> 00:02:40.826
Printed documents
approximately 200 pages.

39
00:02:40.827 --> 00:02:42.328
What's the date range?

40
00:02:42.329 --> 00:02:44.330
Uh. we can catalog that
when we get back.

41
00:02:44.331 --> 00:02:47.083
But I'm seeing
as far back as 1947

42
00:02:47.084 --> 00:02:49.336
and as recent as last year.

43
00:02:50.462 --> 00:02:52.463
(door creaks open)

44
00:02:52.464 --> 00:02:54.674
(lively crowd chatter
in distance)

45
00:02:59.846 --> 00:03:01.848
♪ ♪

46
00:03:15.362 --> 00:03:17.614
(breathing heavily)

47
00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:31.503
Well. this is all
rather disappointing.

48
00:03:34.047 --> 00:03:35.590
Where's Jane?

49
00:03:39.219 --> 00:03:41.430
(trembling breaths)

50
00:03:46.101 --> 00:03:47.894
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

51
00:03:49.312 --> 00:03:51.731
- DANIEL: Careful.
- (snips zip tie)

52
00:03:53.608 --> 00:03:55.735
- (Jane whimpering)
- Hey.

53
00:04:02.534 --> 00:04:04.160
Who turned you?

54
00:04:04.161 --> 00:04:08.747
Give me the names. all of them.
and you two can call a cab.

55
00:04:08.748 --> 00:04:10.625
It's here.

56
00:04:30.061 --> 00:04:31.771
(backpack drops to ground)

57
00:04:33.523 --> 00:04:35.025
Where is it?

58
00:04:39.946 --> 00:04:41.655
- Put your weapon on the ground!
- (others shouting)

59
00:04:41.656 --> 00:04:45.075
Do not fire! Do not fire.

60
00:04:45.076 --> 00:04:47.996
If you fire.
it could activate the device.

61
00:04:49.956 --> 00:04:51.958
Loosen your grip. Daniel.

62
00:04:52.751 --> 00:04:55.128
If you squeeze. it activates.
Soften your grip.

63
00:04:56.171 --> 00:04:58.422
Put it down.
You don't know how to use it.

64
00:04:58.423 --> 00:05:00.591
- I know how you used it.
- And it almost killed me.

65
00:05:00.592 --> 00:05:04.011
Now. place the device
on the ground.

66
00:05:04.012 --> 00:05:06.305
I should do to you
what you did to them.

67
00:05:06.306 --> 00:05:08.307
Stand down. Serena.

68
00:05:08.308 --> 00:05:10.977
(breathing heavily)

69
00:05:11.811 --> 00:05:15.147
Do not exert any pressure on it.

70
00:05:15.148 --> 00:05:17.608
Just loosen your grip.

71
00:05:17.609 --> 00:05:19.276
Loosen your grip. That's it.

72
00:05:19.277 --> 00:05:20.820
Just open your hand.

73
00:05:21.947 --> 00:05:23.072
That's it.

74
00:05:23.073 --> 00:05:24.824
Okay. Okay.

75
00:05:26.284 --> 00:05:28.953
Sweep everything into
the backpack and get in the car.

76
00:05:28.954 --> 00:05:30.497
Please. Jane.

77
00:05:32.999 --> 00:05:34.543
Get out.

78
00:05:39.923 --> 00:05:41.966
You're not running
some malware op.

79
00:05:41.967 --> 00:05:44.718
You can't hide behind a screen
in your SCIF.

80
00:05:44.719 --> 00:05:46.178
The world is on the brink.

81
00:05:46.179 --> 00:05:48.347
Do you actually believe
that dumping inventory

82
00:05:48.348 --> 00:05:51.351
will be anything more
than a dangerous distraction?

83
00:05:52.394 --> 00:05:54.145
I watched the interrogations.

84
00:05:54.980 --> 00:05:56.647
History doesn't have
a reset key.

85
00:05:56.648 --> 00:05:58.608
If you do this.
there's no undoing it.

86
00:06:00.527 --> 00:06:02.612
That's the plan.

87
00:06:03.321 --> 00:06:04.531
(engine starts)

88
00:06:06.449 --> 00:06:08.827
(tires squealing)

89
00:06:16.126 --> 00:06:17.877
Boyd.

90
00:06:21.715 --> 00:06:23.883
He sits at a desk.

91
00:06:25.051 --> 00:06:26.970
How did he beat you?

92
00:06:35.645 --> 00:06:37.229
They said you committed treason?

93
00:06:37.230 --> 00:06:39.106
It's not treason.
They're not the government.

94
00:06:39.107 --> 00:06:40.566
and they lie for a living.

95
00:06:40.567 --> 00:06:42.401
What is going on. Daniel?

96
00:06:42.402 --> 00:06:43.736
Their cars have trackers.

97
00:06:43.737 --> 00:06:45.279
We got to get rid of this.

98
00:06:45.280 --> 00:06:46.572
Please just take me home.

99
00:06:46.573 --> 00:06:48.699
They'd be waiting
at your apartment.

100
00:06:48.700 --> 00:06:50.994
Hey. hand me
the clear plastic bag.

101
00:06:54.331 --> 00:06:56.583
Okay. Steer for a second.

102
00:06:58.001 --> 00:07:00.503
Okay. Okay.

103
00:07:03.256 --> 00:07:04.590
(dialing phone)

104
00:07:04.591 --> 00:07:06.925
- Okay. okay.
- (line ringing)

105
00:07:06.926 --> 00:07:08.260
Hugo. I'm clear.

106
00:07:08.261 --> 00:07:10.929
HUGO (over phone):
Daniel. I'm so proud of you.

107
00:07:10.930 --> 00:07:13.307
They kidnapped Jane
to get to me.

108
00:07:13.308 --> 00:07:14.892
She's with me now.

109
00:07:14.893 --> 00:07:16.644
HUGO:
Is she all right?

110
00:07:16.645 --> 00:07:18.395
Not really. Hugo.

111
00:07:18.396 --> 00:07:19.730
Where do I do the drop?

112
00:07:19.731 --> 00:07:21.231
- No drop yet.
- (power tools buzzing)

113
00:07:21.232 --> 00:07:23.442
- Get secure. and then...
- DANIEL: No. no. no.

114
00:07:23.443 --> 00:07:25.444
Send the guy for the bag now.

115
00:07:25.445 --> 00:07:27.279
Somebody needs to run
with this thing.

116
00:07:27.280 --> 00:07:28.614
That's you.

117
00:07:28.615 --> 00:07:30.116
You've got the ball.

118
00:07:31.201 --> 00:07:32.910
I don't want the ball.

119
00:07:32.911 --> 00:07:35.788
No. the plan was I get it out
of the facility. and I-I did.

120
00:07:35.789 --> 00:07:37.456
HUGO: I decided
you were best qualified

121
00:07:37.457 --> 00:07:38.791
to keep the material safe.

122
00:07:38.792 --> 00:07:40.834
Are you out of your mind?

123
00:07:40.835 --> 00:07:43.295
No. I'm not a field guy. Hugo.

124
00:07:43.296 --> 00:07:45.714
I-I did the tech work.
That's all I can do.

125
00:07:45.715 --> 00:07:47.049
You just stay with me.

126
00:07:47.050 --> 00:07:48.258
We're on plan.

127
00:07:48.259 --> 00:07:50.886
Waiting now for someone else
to be activated.

128
00:07:50.887 --> 00:07:53.180
When they are.
we'll know what comes next.

129
00:07:53.181 --> 00:07:55.974
Leave Jane somewhere safe
and get secure for the night.

130
00:07:55.975 --> 00:07:58.727
Oh. no.
I-I'm not leaving her alone.

131
00:07:58.728 --> 00:08:01.271
- She'll be safer without you.
- But she wasn't.

132
00:08:01.272 --> 00:08:04.274
I'm gonna need you to drop
a marker when you get secure.

133
00:08:04.275 --> 00:08:06.735
Our friend Santiago
will find you in the morning.

134
00:08:06.736 --> 00:08:10.156
I should just dump everything
online right now.

135
00:08:11.741 --> 00:08:15.078
You cannot. under any
circumstances. do that.

136
00:08:16.579 --> 00:08:17.913
For now. we wait.

137
00:08:17.914 --> 00:08:19.832
Stay alert. Find shelter.

138
00:08:19.833 --> 00:08:22.127
Santiago will put us together
in the morning.

139
00:08:23.128 --> 00:08:24.420
Destroy your phone.

140
00:08:24.421 --> 00:08:25.754
(sighs)

141
00:08:25.755 --> 00:08:27.423
(siren wailing in distance)

142
00:08:27.424 --> 00:08:28.799
Danny.

143
00:08:28.800 --> 00:08:31.051
Satellite burner phones.

144
00:08:31.052 --> 00:08:32.720
They got their own
encrypted network.

145
00:08:32.721 --> 00:08:34.764
We only use them once.

146
00:08:37.016 --> 00:08:39.519
What exactly do you do
for a living?

147
00:08:40.645 --> 00:08:42.354
We got to get secure
for the night.

148
00:08:42.355 --> 00:08:44.106
No apartments. no motels.

149
00:08:44.107 --> 00:08:47.110
Has to be somewhere I've never
been before in my life.

150
00:08:48.361 --> 00:08:50.864
I know a place close to here.

151
00:09:02.500 --> 00:09:03.751
(elevator bell chimes)

152
00:09:03.752 --> 00:09:06.712
Musgrave at DoD wants
a briefing.

153
00:09:06.713 --> 00:09:08.881
SCANLON:
Get Wakefield down here now.

154
00:09:08.882 --> 00:09:10.758
Tell Musgrave
it was a minor breach.

155
00:09:10.759 --> 00:09:12.176
Recovery is in process.

156
00:09:12.177 --> 00:09:14.094
Sir. he will not want
to hear it from me.

157
00:09:14.095 --> 00:09:16.221
If I pick up the phone.
it means I'm concerned.

158
00:09:16.222 --> 00:09:18.140
If they even get a whiff
of that. we'll have the entire

159
00:09:18.141 --> 00:09:20.684
military and intelligence
apparatus up here in an hour.

160
00:09:20.685 --> 00:09:21.977
Handle him.

161
00:09:21.978 --> 00:09:23.937
Anything relevant to this
on news feeds?

162
00:09:23.938 --> 00:09:25.022
Not yet.

163
00:09:25.023 --> 00:09:26.774
Socials or secure private?

164
00:09:26.775 --> 00:09:28.651
All quiet.

165
00:09:31.738 --> 00:09:33.865
12 no-shows here today.

166
00:09:37.243 --> 00:09:39.244
All with empty desks.

167
00:09:39.245 --> 00:09:41.580
All clearance above G5.

168
00:09:41.581 --> 00:09:43.792
(busy chatter)

169
00:09:50.006 --> 00:09:52.841
All right. so we're dealing
with an operation

170
00:09:52.842 --> 00:09:56.137
carefully coordinated
and executed.

171
00:09:57.430 --> 00:10:00.057
Why? With what goal?

172
00:10:00.058 --> 00:10:01.725
If they wanted the archive out.

173
00:10:01.726 --> 00:10:03.310
Kellner would have
already released it.

174
00:10:03.311 --> 00:10:04.728
but he hasn't. which means

175
00:10:04.729 --> 00:10:06.355
somebody's maintaining
decision space.

176
00:10:06.356 --> 00:10:10.442
But for how long. we don't know.
so think quickly.

177
00:10:10.443 --> 00:10:11.902
Daniel Kellner has a doctorate

178
00:10:11.903 --> 00:10:13.779
in theoretical
and applied cybersecurity.

179
00:10:13.780 --> 00:10:15.614
and he's spent the better part
of eight years

180
00:10:15.615 --> 00:10:17.115
safeguarding high-side data.

181
00:10:17.116 --> 00:10:19.284
so what does that
tell us about him?

182
00:10:19.285 --> 00:10:20.244
Ideas.

183
00:10:20.245 --> 00:10:21.578
- Come on.
- He built the firewalls.

184
00:10:21.579 --> 00:10:22.996
He knows how to breach them.

185
00:10:22.997 --> 00:10:24.456
They're already breached.
We got to play past that.

186
00:10:24.457 --> 00:10:25.999
AGENT: We got to maintain
standard skip tracing.

187
00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:27.334
AGENT 2:
Well. I can access SYNTRAK.

188
00:10:27.335 --> 00:10:29.336
SERENA:
What's the next thing he does?

189
00:10:29.337 --> 00:10:31.380
BOYD:
Sir.

190
00:10:31.381 --> 00:10:34.676
Hugo Wakefield didn't show up
for work this morning.

191
00:10:36.135 --> 00:10:39.221
(sighs)
His desk was cleaned out.

192
00:10:39.222 --> 00:10:40.932
Hugo?

193
00:10:43.810 --> 00:10:47.229
Second device is missing
from deep storage.

194
00:10:47.230 --> 00:10:48.897
Where's the third?

195
00:10:48.898 --> 00:10:50.942
Locked down in the cold room.

196
00:10:54.779 --> 00:10:56.990
♪ ♪

197
00:11:16.801 --> 00:11:19.012
♪ ♪

198
00:11:26.019 --> 00:11:27.395
(vehicle door closes)

199
00:11:31.316 --> 00:11:34.443
DANIEL: How do you know
they'll answer it?

200
00:11:34.444 --> 00:11:36.237
'Cause that's what we do.

201
00:11:37.030 --> 00:11:39.032
How do you know this place?

202
00:11:43.494 --> 00:11:45.038
Jane.

203
00:11:46.039 --> 00:11:49.125
(sobbing):
Oh... oh. my dear.

204
00:11:53.046 --> 00:11:55.714
The monsignor has finally
surrendered his sneakers.

205
00:11:55.715 --> 00:11:57.090
- Oh.
- (chuckling)

206
00:11:57.091 --> 00:11:58.592
Oh. I couldn't bear
his other shoes.

207
00:11:58.593 --> 00:12:01.261
I know. They always
squeaked so horribly.

208
00:12:01.262 --> 00:12:02.220
(both laughing)

209
00:12:02.221 --> 00:12:04.890
(imitating squeaking footsteps)

210
00:12:04.891 --> 00:12:08.560
Oh. we have missed you
very much. my dear.

211
00:12:08.561 --> 00:12:10.228
Oh. come on.

212
00:12:10.229 --> 00:12:12.147
All I ever did was drive you
and the other sisters crazy.

213
00:12:12.148 --> 00:12:15.901
Mm. well. you do ask
a lot of questions.

214
00:12:15.902 --> 00:12:17.945
Did Teresa ever get through
her postulancy?

215
00:12:17.946 --> 00:12:19.279
She sailed through.

216
00:12:19.280 --> 00:12:21.615
Once she stopped
sneaking out at night.

217
00:12:21.616 --> 00:12:23.075
JANE:
No.

218
00:12:23.076 --> 00:12:24.201
SISTER MAURA:
The monsignor has her teaching

219
00:12:24.202 --> 00:12:26.119
third grade at St. Anthony's.

220
00:12:26.120 --> 00:12:28.580
JANE: Oh. she'll be
fantastic with kids.

221
00:12:28.581 --> 00:12:31.000
BOTH:
Saint Benedicta.

222
00:12:33.252 --> 00:12:36.422
Hold this against your eye.

223
00:12:43.888 --> 00:12:46.139
I'm not going to ask you
any questions.

224
00:12:46.140 --> 00:12:47.766
It's not my business.

225
00:12:47.767 --> 00:12:49.769
But Jane is.

226
00:12:50.603 --> 00:12:54.648
Whatever you have done. you must
hold yourself accountable.

227
00:12:54.649 --> 00:12:57.818
But leave Jane out of it.

228
00:12:57.819 --> 00:13:00.279
She can stay with us.

229
00:13:04.951 --> 00:13:06.869
(chuckling):
You were a nun?

230
00:13:07.996 --> 00:13:10.497
We've had sex.
What do you think?

231
00:13:10.498 --> 00:13:14.293
I think everything you told me
about yourself isn't true.

232
00:13:15.336 --> 00:13:17.713
You have an enormous
amount of nerve.

233
00:13:17.714 --> 00:13:19.673
Yeah. I kept things to myself

234
00:13:19.674 --> 00:13:22.467
because I had to sign away
my life. but your thing...

235
00:13:22.468 --> 00:13:25.512
(chuckles)
You were an actual nun?

236
00:13:25.513 --> 00:13:27.264
A novitiate.

237
00:13:27.265 --> 00:13:28.640
Why didn't you say anything?

238
00:13:28.641 --> 00:13:30.017
I omitted a portion of my story.

239
00:13:30.018 --> 00:13:31.310
People judge you.

240
00:13:34.063 --> 00:13:36.232
When was all this?

241
00:13:37.025 --> 00:13:38.567
Three years ago.

242
00:13:38.568 --> 00:13:41.988
And I'm not answering
any more questions until you do.

243
00:13:43.531 --> 00:13:45.199
What did you steal?

244
00:13:47.326 --> 00:13:50.162
I stole the data
they paid me to protect.

245
00:13:50.163 --> 00:13:52.206
Why would you do that?

246
00:13:53.166 --> 00:13:55.293
'Cause people have a right
to know the truth.

247
00:13:56.210 --> 00:13:59.547
And what is it.
this truth you stole?

248
00:14:01.716 --> 00:14:03.508
So...

249
00:14:03.509 --> 00:14:07.847
you wanted to be a nun.
but what. you lost your faith?

250
00:14:08.639 --> 00:14:10.265
I lost my calling.

251
00:14:10.266 --> 00:14:13.393
How long have you worked
for these people?

252
00:14:13.394 --> 00:14:15.188
Since. um...

253
00:14:18.900 --> 00:14:21.193
Since I got out...

254
00:14:21.194 --> 00:14:23.571
of federal prison
eight years ago.

255
00:14:27.325 --> 00:14:31.828
I did 19 months in Petersburg
for cybercrimes.

256
00:14:31.829 --> 00:14:34.539
WARDEX recruited me
straight out of the parking lot

257
00:14:34.540 --> 00:14:36.374
the day I was released.

258
00:14:36.375 --> 00:14:39.045
- Even with your record?
- Because of my record.

259
00:14:39.879 --> 00:14:41.254
I keep secrets for a living.

260
00:14:41.255 --> 00:14:44.591
I-I didn't mean
to keep them from you.

261
00:14:44.592 --> 00:14:48.429
Three months ago. I didn't know
half of what I know now.

262
00:14:49.931 --> 00:14:51.516
Jane...

263
