00:35:11.276 --> 00:35:12.443
- We're leaving. We're leaving.
- What?

754
00:35:12.444 --> 00:35:13.694
- Got to go. Got to go.
- What?

755
00:35:13.695 --> 00:35:15.154
- Got to go.
- What are you talk...

756
00:35:15.155 --> 00:35:16.405
- Oh. God. I'm so sorry.
- Hi. Uh...

757
00:35:16.406 --> 00:35:17.573
- Excuse me.
- What do you mean?

758
00:35:17.574 --> 00:35:19.116
- You mean busting out?
- Yep.

759
00:35:19.117 --> 00:35:20.617
- Wh-What's wrong with you?
- What's wrong is I have

760
00:35:20.618 --> 00:35:22.662
a very uncooperative
boyfriend right...

761
00:35:25.832 --> 00:35:28.625
- Oh. you got to be kidding me.
- What? What did I do?

762
00:35:28.626 --> 00:35:30.294
You know exactly
what I'm talking about.

763
00:35:30.295 --> 00:35:32.297
What did I do? Maggie.

764
00:35:33.340 --> 00:35:34.798
Shoes. Shoes. shoes.

765
00:35:34.799 --> 00:35:36.300
Yeah. sure.

766
00:35:36.301 --> 00:35:38.219
- Here.
- Thank you.

767
00:35:40.180 --> 00:35:42.349
How's it going?

768
00:35:50.273 --> 00:35:52.484
♪ ♪

769
00:36:00.283 --> 00:36:01.909
WARDEX?

770
00:36:01.910 --> 00:36:05.663
Stands for Waived Reporting
Development and Extraction.

771
00:36:06.873 --> 00:36:08.541
Of what?

772
00:36:25.475 --> 00:36:29.604
Homestead Air Force Base
in Florida. 1973.

773
00:36:30.480 --> 00:36:32.272
Who's the guy with Nixon?

774
00:36:32.273 --> 00:36:34.108
Big TV star in the '50s.

775
00:36:34.109 --> 00:36:36.194
Nixon wanted to impress him.

776
00:36:45.203 --> 00:36:47.414
♪ ♪

777
00:37:06.808 --> 00:37:08.852
♪ ♪

778
00:37:23.908 --> 00:37:25.742
Are they children?

779
00:37:25.743 --> 00:37:27.370
No.

780
00:37:30.248 --> 00:37:33.292
Are they... people?

781
00:37:33.293 --> 00:37:35.336
No.

782
00:37:38.798 --> 00:37:40.550
Are they human?

783
00:37:53.438 --> 00:37:55.732
This next part's hard to watch.

784
00:37:56.983 --> 00:38:00.028
It's what Hugo showed me
that got me into this.

785
00:38:01.696 --> 00:38:02.864
Okay?

786
00:38:08.745 --> 00:38:10.330
Okay.

787
00:38:11.748 --> 00:38:12.998
(taps key)

788
00:38:12.999 --> 00:38:14.791
MED TECH 1 (on video):
We're gonna need vitals.

789
00:38:14.792 --> 00:38:16.418
- We've got no baseline.
- (overlapping chatter on video)

790
00:38:16.419 --> 00:38:17.836
MED TECH 2:
Pulse ox can't read.

791
00:38:17.837 --> 00:38:19.546
- No standard landmarks...
- MED TECH 3: Ketamine?

792
00:38:19.547 --> 00:38:20.923
- Four to six milligrams?
- SCANLON: No more sedatives.

793
00:38:20.924 --> 00:38:22.674
I want baseline
stress data first.

794
00:38:22.675 --> 00:38:24.676
MED TECH 4: Shift your grip.
Secure the ankles.

795
00:38:24.677 --> 00:38:27.304
- (clicking vocalizations)
- Stabilize head and right arm.

796
00:38:27.305 --> 00:38:29.598
(shrieks)

797
00:38:29.599 --> 00:38:31.600
(distressed shrieking. clicking)

798
00:38:31.601 --> 00:38:33.143
MED TECH 3:
Head's moving too much.

799
00:38:33.144 --> 00:38:34.645
I need a padded restraint.

800
00:38:34.646 --> 00:38:36.813
SCANLON: I have it.
I need cerebrospinal fluid.

801
00:38:36.814 --> 00:38:39.149
Advance the needle
18 centimeters.

802
00:38:39.150 --> 00:38:40.943
- ventral to the medulla.
- (shuddering breaths)

803
00:38:40.944 --> 00:38:43.320
MED TECH 1: It's in distress.
Administering propofol.

804
00:38:43.321 --> 00:38:45.405
SCANLON:
Negative. No anesthesia.

805
00:38:45.406 --> 00:38:47.491
We lost one that way. Do it now.

806
00:38:47.492 --> 00:38:48.951
Insert it now.

807
00:38:48.952 --> 00:38:50.911
(pained shrieking)

808
00:38:50.912 --> 00:38:52.496
(shrieking stops)

809
00:38:52.497 --> 00:38:55.750
(shuddering breaths)

810
00:39:04.926 --> 00:39:06.343
There's more.

811
00:39:06.344 --> 00:39:09.597
79 years more.

812
00:39:11.432 --> 00:39:13.308
I have all of it.

813
00:39:13.309 --> 00:39:15.937
(whirring)

814
00:39:18.189 --> 00:39:20.400
(electronic trilling)

815
00:39:21.943 --> 00:39:24.112
(buzzing)

816
00:39:35.331 --> 00:39:38.792
Hugo is the only one
who had a relationship with it.

817
00:39:38.793 --> 00:39:41.420
and he knew what he was doing
with that thing.

818
00:39:41.421 --> 00:39:43.590
Pull up Kellner's data.

819
00:39:48.636 --> 00:39:50.262
Give me the device.

820
00:39:50.263 --> 00:39:51.722
BOYD:
If systolic goes below 90

821
00:39:51.723 --> 00:39:53.098
like last time.
I'm pulling you out.

822
00:39:53.099 --> 00:39:54.683
MED TECH:
Watch for tachyarrhythmia.

823
00:39:54.684 --> 00:39:56.518
- subdural hemorrhage.
- MED TECH 2: Copy.

824
00:39:56.519 --> 00:39:58.980
(monitor beeping)

825
00:40:00.315 --> 00:40:02.316
(quiet chatter)

826
00:40:02.317 --> 00:40:04.569
♪ ♪

827
00:40:12.243 --> 00:40:14.912
(beeping growing faster)

828
00:40:16.956 --> 00:40:18.206
(whimpers)

829
00:40:18.207 --> 00:40:20.792
(yells. groans)

830
00:40:20.793 --> 00:40:23.211
I'm fine. I'm fine!

831
00:40:23.212 --> 00:40:24.881
What happened?

832
00:40:26.924 --> 00:40:29.217
I had focus. gave myself over.

833
00:40:29.218 --> 00:40:32.304
saw Kellner for a split second.
then...

834
00:40:32.305 --> 00:40:33.764
sledgehammer. whiteout.

835
00:40:33.765 --> 00:40:36.433
Sucked all the air
out of my lungs.

836
00:40:36.434 --> 00:40:38.477
Is he an experiencer?

837
00:40:38.478 --> 00:40:40.188
You can't dive on them.

838
00:40:42.440 --> 00:40:45.025
He can't have been.
I'd have known.

839
00:40:45.026 --> 00:40:46.610
He's Hugo's guy.

840
00:40:46.611 --> 00:40:48.945
There's gonna be a whole lot
we don't know.

841
00:40:48.946 --> 00:40:51.866
Maybe. but I'm not going
back in there to find out.

842
00:41:01.793 --> 00:41:04.128
Pull the data on the girlfriend.

843
00:41:05.338 --> 00:41:09.300
There have been retrieval
programs of exotic craft.

844
00:41:10.134 --> 00:41:13.804
Interrogation
of nonhuman biologics.

845
00:41:13.805 --> 00:41:17.140
Reverse engineering
and technology exploitation.

846
00:41:17.141 --> 00:41:18.642
All of it...

847
00:41:18.643 --> 00:41:21.645
run by WARDEX.
the Department of Defense

848
00:41:21.646 --> 00:41:23.814
and the defense industry.

849
00:41:23.815 --> 00:41:26.483
It has the highest level
of military

850
00:41:26.484 --> 00:41:28.151
and private sector
classification

851
00:41:28.152 --> 00:41:29.486
in American history.

852
00:41:29.487 --> 00:41:30.779
(wind howling outside)

853
00:41:30.780 --> 00:41:32.322
They've run it
since the early '70s

854
00:41:32.323 --> 00:41:33.657
without government funding.

855
00:41:33.658 --> 00:41:35.742
Too many tax dollars
to try and hide.

856
00:41:35.743 --> 00:41:38.161
and-and off-world artifacts
are too profitable

857
00:41:38.162 --> 00:41:39.955
to leave in the hands
of appointed officials.

858
00:41:39.956 --> 00:41:42.833
especially after
the Nixon thing.

859
00:41:42.834 --> 00:41:46.461
Presidents are civilians again
after eight years. so...

860
00:41:46.462 --> 00:41:50.007
so there's no longer a reason
to read them in on any of this.

861
00:41:51.884 --> 00:41:55.513
I was a part of all that
until I saw what you just saw.

862
00:41:56.431 --> 00:41:59.850
This all stops now.

863
00:41:59.851 --> 00:42:01.519
What are you gonna do?

864
00:42:02.353 --> 00:42:07.191
Full disclosure
to the whole world all at once.

865
00:42:09.861 --> 00:42:12.989
Have you considered
what effect that'll have?

866
00:42:14.157 --> 00:42:15.867
On everything?

867
00:42:16.701 --> 00:42:18.076
What...

868
00:42:18.077 --> 00:42:19.953
It's not up to me
to decide if it's...

869
00:42:19.954 --> 00:42:22.914
if it's good or bad
for people to know.

870
00:42:22.915 --> 00:42:25.792
Then how is it up to you
to decide that the right to know

871
00:42:25.793 --> 00:42:28.128
outweighs the consequences
of knowing?

872
00:42:28.129 --> 00:42:30.046
Are you saying
we leave this up to WARDEX?

873
00:42:30.047 --> 00:42:32.674
'Cause they-they've already
decided this belongs to them.

874
00:42:32.675 --> 00:42:35.260
this core truth
about the universe.

875
00:42:35.261 --> 00:42:37.764
- It's wrong.
- You can't do that.

876
00:42:38.723 --> 00:42:40.641
Think about...

877
00:42:41.934 --> 00:42:43.602
People will see them as deities.

878
00:42:43.603 --> 00:42:45.645
- They'll stop believing in God.
- (scoffs)

879
00:42:45.646 --> 00:42:47.564
Well. you left the church.

880
00:42:47.565 --> 00:42:48.982
Not because I stopped believing.

881
00:42:48.983 --> 00:42:50.692
because I could no longer say
with certainty

882
00:42:50.693 --> 00:42:52.068
that God is divine.

883
00:42:52.069 --> 00:42:55.573
but I believe profoundly
that he's essential.

884
00:42:56.949 --> 00:42:58.450
He's how we define ourselves.

885
00:42:58.451 --> 00:43:01.788
He's what keeps
whole civilizations together.

886
00:43:03.039 --> 00:43:05.916
We've been raised to believe
in a supreme being.

887
00:43:05.917 --> 00:43:09.795
and now you want to show us
actual supreme beings?

888
00:43:09.796 --> 00:43:11.756
People can't handle both.

889
00:43:14.217 --> 00:43:15.842
Of course they can.

890
00:43:15.843 --> 00:43:17.470
No. they can't.

891
00:43:18.262 --> 00:43:20.431
Look at our history
with any sudden change.

892
00:43:21.265 --> 00:43:25.895
And now. with the world about
to blow up in all our faces?

893
00:43:27.104 --> 00:43:31.943
You'll get panic and-and chaos.
and God help us.

894
00:43:35.947 --> 00:43:38.241
Hugo's expecting me to check in.

895
00:43:50.086 --> 00:43:51.796
No signal.

896
00:43:53.464 --> 00:43:55.131
No signal.

897
00:43:55.132 --> 00:43:57.635
I'll try the other side
of the hill.

898
00:44:10.690 --> 00:44:13.150
(door opens and closes)

899
00:44:14.902 --> 00:44:17.196
(Jackson grunting. panting)

900
00:44:22.326 --> 00:44:24.328
(thunder rumbling)

901
00:44:27.498 --> 00:44:28.707
- Okay.
- (knocking)

902
00:44:28.708 --> 00:44:30.041
- Unlock the door!
- (engine starts)

903
00:44:30.042 --> 00:44:31.334
- What?
- Jackson. come on!

904
00:44:31.335 --> 00:44:33.254
- (lock clicks)
- Oh. shit. Sorry.

905
00:44:34.380 --> 00:44:36.047
Oh. sorry. sorry.

906
00:44:36.048 --> 00:44:38.801
- Okay.
- Oh. my God.

907
00:44:40.428 --> 00:44:42.846
(phone ringing)

908
00:44:42.847 --> 00:44:44.264
(Jackson stammers)

909
00:44:44.265 --> 00:44:45.974
If you answer that in French.
I swear to God

910
00:44:45.975 --> 00:44:47.517
I'm marching you
right back inside.

911
00:44:47.518 --> 00:44:49.019
Hello?

912
00:44:49.020 --> 00:44:51.021
HUGO (over phone): I've been
waiting a very long time

913
00:44:51.022 --> 00:44:53.440
to meet you. Ms. Fairchild.

914
00:44:53.441 --> 00:44:55.108
Who is this?

915
00:44:55.109 --> 00:44:56.861
A friend.

916
00:44:57.778 --> 00:45:00.655
And if I'm right about you.
Margaret.

917
00:45:00.656 --> 00:45:02.073
you'd know if I wasn't.

918
00:45:02.074 --> 00:45:03.533
No. I don't... I don't know you

919
00:45:03.534 --> 00:45:05.410
any more than I know
what's happening to me.

920
00:45:05.411 --> 00:45:07.871
HUGO: Very few people could
manage this as well as you.

921
00:45:07.872 --> 00:45:09.539
- I'm not managing it. I'm not.
- Who-who is that?

922
00:45:09.540 --> 00:45:12.042
I am frightened.
I'm frightened out of my wits.

923
00:45:12.043 --> 00:45:16.171
Because you're just a passenger
on your way somewhere.

924
00:45:16.172 --> 00:45:18.214
- Let us help you get there.
- Help me how?

925
00:45:18.215 --> 00:45:19.090
What do you mean?

926
00:45:19.091 --> 00:45:20.508
- Is that the FBI?
- Shh!

927
00:45:20.509 --> 00:45:21.885
HUGO: We want to offer you
our protection.

928
00:45:21.886 --> 00:45:23.261
We held back on reaching out

929
00:45:23.262 --> 00:45:25.555
until after we saw
your weather report.

930
00:45:25.556 --> 00:45:26.806
You held back?

931
00:45:26.807 --> 00:45:28.016
What do you mean?
What does that mean?

932
00:45:28.017 --> 00:45:30.061
Are you gonna need a lawyer?

933
00:45:33.648 --> 00:45:36.734
Who is 873-2626?

934
00:45:38.069 --> 00:45:39.444
Since you know that number.

935
00:45:39.445 --> 00:45:42.114
you must already know
who it belongs to.

936
00:45:44.408 --> 00:45:45.785
Kellner?

937
00:45:46.577 --> 00:45:47.619
Kellner?

938
00:45:47.620 --> 00:45:49.537
All right.

939
00:45:49.538 --> 00:45:51.039
Listen carefully.

940
00:45:51.040 --> 00:45:52.290
You cannot go home.

941
00:45:52.291 --> 00:45:53.792
If you have another direction
in mind.

942
00:45:53.793 --> 00:45:56.086
even a vague inclination.
follow it.

943
00:45:56.087 --> 00:45:57.963
If we can find you by phone.
others can

944
00:45:57.964 --> 00:45:59.839
- find you in the world.
- No. it's too late.

945
00:45:59.840 --> 00:46:01.216
They...
Uh. they already found me.

946
00:46:01.217 --> 00:46:04.052
Hang up immediately.
Destroy your phone.

947
00:46:04.053 --> 00:46:05.470
How will you find me?

948
00:46:05.471 --> 00:46:06.930
I have every confidence
you'll find us.

949
00:46:06.931 --> 00:46:08.140
Do it now.

950
00:46:09.600 --> 00:46:12.812
Wait. wait. What are you...
Wh-What are you doing?!

951
00:46:14.105 --> 00:46:15.397
Back up over the phone.

952
00:46:15.398 --> 00:46:16.815
- What?
- Back up!

953
00:46:16.816 --> 00:46:18.441
- Come on. -Okay. I'd like
to point out that I'm being

954
00:46:18.442 --> 00:46:21.069
extremely cool here
and that I'm rolling with it.

955
00:46:21.070 --> 00:46:23.280
and that was a $600 phone.

956
00:46:24.115 --> 00:46:26.116
Well. it's still a $600 phone
'cause you missed it.

957
00:46:26.117 --> 00:46:27.742
Jackson. pull forward
till you hear the crunch.

958
00:46:27.743 --> 00:46:28.953
- Come on.
- Sorry.

959
00:46:33.165 --> 00:46:35.583
Oh. my God. you missed it again.
Oh. my God.

960
00:46:35.584 --> 00:46:37.795
- Okay. (mutters)
- What?

961
00:46:41.424 --> 00:46:42.883
Okay.

962
00:46:44.218 --> 00:46:46.971
Pull forward. Go. go. go.

963
00:46:48.222 --> 00:46:50.266
Keep going. Keep going.

964
00:46:59.483 --> 00:47:01.609
Okay. Okay.

965
00:47:01.610 --> 00:47:05.155
- Okay. let's go. Let's go.
- Uh... wh-where?

966
00:47:05.156 --> 00:47:06.656
- North.
- Why?

967
00:47:06.657 --> 00:47:08.116
Because that's where
Daniel Kellner is.

968
00:47:08.117 --> 00:47:09.534
Oh. my God. (stammering)

969
00:47:09.535 --> 00:47:11.327
Who is this dude?
Is he some guy from your past

970
00:47:11.328 --> 00:47:12.996
- that you never told me about?
- I don't know. Jackson.

971
00:47:12.997 --> 00:47:14.247
- Or what is it?
- You're giving me a headache.

972
00:47:14.248 --> 00:47:15.206
I don't know
what I'm doing here.

973
00:47:15.207 --> 00:47:16.499
I don't know who he is.

974
00:47:16.500 --> 00:47:18.126
I just know
he's someplace north.

975
00:47:18.127 --> 00:47:19.210
- That's all I know. okay?
- (hailstones clacking)

976
00:47:19.211 --> 00:47:20.963
Oh. my God. What is that sound?

977
00:47:23.090 --> 00:47:25.425
- Your hailstorm.
- Wow.

978
00:47:25.426 --> 00:47:26.801
Weather Shimmy?

979
00:47:26.802 --> 00:47:29.180
Just drive. Just drive.

980
00:47:38.731 --> 00:47:41.066
(electronic trilling. beeping)

981
00:47:41.067 --> 00:47:43.319
♪ ♪

982
00:48:08.886 --> 00:48:10.888
(sighs)

983
00:48:11.639 --> 00:48:13.056
(electronic warbling)

984
00:48:13.057 --> 00:48:15.226
(crate thuds on table)

985
00:48:17.603 --> 00:48:20.231
You got Kellner on 2626.

986
00:48:21.816 --> 00:48:23.399
Look at the video
I just sent you.

987
00:48:23.400 --> 00:48:25.069
DANIEL (over phone):
Okay. hold on.

988
00:48:26.987 --> 00:48:29.240
(Margaret clicking tongue
on video)

989
00:48:31.450 --> 00:48:32.700
Yeah. So?

990
00:48:32.701 --> 00:48:34.869
She's the one
we've been waiting for.

991
00:48:34.870 --> 00:48:37.247
DANIEL:
Her? Why?

992
00:48:37.248 --> 00:48:39.541
Did you not hear her?

993
00:48:39.542 --> 00:48:41.126
DANIEL:
Yeah. I heard her.

994
00:48:41.127 --> 00:48:42.502
And you still ask why?

995
00:48:42.503 --> 00:48:44.420
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

996
00:48:44.421 --> 00:48:46.423
That's all she had to say?

997
00:48:47.591 --> 00:48:49.884
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

998
00:48:49.885 --> 00:48:51.219
That's what she said?

999
00:48:51.220 --> 00:48:53.055
You didn't hear it?

1000
00:48:54.431 --> 00:48:55.723
We all heard it.

1001
00:48:55.724 --> 00:48:58.101
We couldn't understand it.
It's not English.

1002
00:48:58.102 --> 00:48:59.853
(chuckling):
Of course it is.

1003
00:48:59.854 --> 00:49:01.688
I'm listening to it right now.

1004
00:49:01.689 --> 00:49:03.606
I'm sending you to Kansas City.
where she's from.

1005
00:49:03.607 --> 00:49:05.692
- We'll get a car to you.
Leave tonight. -Hey. wait.

1006
00:49:05.693 --> 00:49:07.318
- Wait a second. Wait a second.
- Do not travel by day.

1007
00:49:07.319 --> 00:49:08.611
You're not hearing it?
It's-it's perfectly clear.

1008
00:49:08.612 --> 00:49:09.946
Detour past tollbooths
and turnpikes.

1009
00:49:09.947 --> 00:49:11.197
DANIEL:
Hey. listen to me.

1010
00:49:11.198 --> 00:49:12.615
Have you played this
to other people?

1011
00:49:12.616 --> 00:49:14.492
Stay with me.

1012
00:49:14.493 --> 00:49:17.287
A motel room key will be
in the car with directions.

1013
00:49:17.288 --> 00:49:19.289
Santiago will retrieve you
in the morning.

1014
00:49:19.290 --> 00:49:21.708
By then. I'll know
what comes next.

1015
00:49:21.709 --> 00:49:24.460
Hugo. you're scaring
the shit out of me.

1016
00:49:24.461 --> 00:49:28.298
There are two of you. Daniel.

1017
00:49:28.299 --> 00:49:31.676
There's always been
just the two of you.

1018
00:49:31.677 --> 00:49:33.678
(rustling)

1019
00:49:33.679 --> 00:49:35.723
♪ ♪

1020
00:49:59.830 --> 00:50:01.665
(breathing heavily)

1021
00:50:03.042 --> 00:50:05.336
(pills rattling)

1022
00:50:10.883 --> 00:50:13.676
(gasping)

1023
00:50:13.677 --> 00:50:16.096
(trembling breaths)

1024
00:50:20.851 --> 00:50:22.353
(exhales slowly)

1025
00:50:24.939 --> 00:50:27.191
(trembling breaths continue)

1026
00:50:28.609 --> 00:50:30.402
(whirring)

1027
00:50:40.955 --> 00:50:43.540
♪ ♪

1028
00:50:44.416 --> 00:50:47.086
(muffled shattering)

1029
00:50:56.220 --> 00:50:59.181
(glass shards clinking)

1030
00:51:18.575 --> 00:51:20.619
♪ ♪

1031
00:51:30.296 --> 00:51:32.255
- (hands clap)
- (gasps)

1032
00:51:32.256 --> 00:51:34.550
(sharp. heavy breathing)

1033
00:51:40.431 --> 00:51:42.683
(praying in Latin)

1034
00:52:00.284 --> 00:52:02.536
♪ ♪

1035
00:52:26.894 --> 00:52:28.644
Hello. Jane.

1036
00:52:28.645 --> 00:52:30.481
Please.

1037
00:52:31.732 --> 00:52:33.776
Have a seat.

1038
00:52:39.281 --> 00:52:42.033
Where are you right now. Jane?

1039
00:52:42.034 --> 00:52:43.827
What is your location?

1040
00:52:44.828 --> 00:52:47.498
- I don't know.
- Relax. please.

1041
00:52:50.584 --> 00:52:53.462
- Who are you?
- I'll ask the questions.

1042
00:52:54.254 --> 00:52:56.298
Are you still with
Daniel Kellner?

1043
00:53:02.221 --> 00:53:03.680
He's outside.

1044
00:53:07.184 --> 00:53:08.894
Where were you last night?

1045
00:53:10.521 --> 00:53:12.773
(breath trembling)

1046
00:53:14.900 --> 00:53:16.275
(snarls)

1047
00:53:16.276 --> 00:53:18.152
(panting)

1048
00:53:18.153 --> 00:53:20.947
- BP's high but holding: 156/94.
- O2's decent at 96.

1049
00:53:20.948 --> 00:53:22.949
- but sodium's climbing.
- Heart rate's hot. too-- 118.

1050
00:53:22.950 --> 00:53:24.325
- Potassium's borderline. too.
- Jane!

1051
00:53:24.326 --> 00:53:25.953
- Stand by. Ringer's.
- Jane!

1052
00:53:26.912 --> 00:53:28.413
- Jane!
- (gasps)

1053
00:53:28.414 --> 00:53:30.874
Where were you last night?

1054
00:53:31.834 --> 00:53:35.044
Monastery of St. Clare
of the Dawn.

1055
00:53:35.045 --> 00:53:37.255
Monastery St. Clare?

1056
00:53:37.256 --> 00:53:38.714
Of course.

1057
00:53:38.715 --> 00:53:41.759
I remember St. Clare
from my Sunday school.

1058
00:53:41.760 --> 00:53:43.845
She was too sick to go
to midnight Mass.

1059
00:53:43.846 --> 00:53:46.556
and she had a vision
of it instead.

1060
00:53:46.557 --> 00:53:49.393
She was in two places at once.
like me.

1061
00:53:51.770 --> 00:53:53.896
Monastery of St. Clare. Got it.

1062
00:53:53.897 --> 00:53:55.940
13 miles southeast
of the District.

1063
00:53:55.941 --> 00:53:58.735
When you left.
which way did you drive?

1064
00:53:59.653 --> 00:54:02.280
(Jane's breath trembling)

1065
00:54:02.281 --> 00:54:03.781
I don't know.

1066
00:54:03.782 --> 00:54:05.409
Was the sun up?

1067
00:54:08.287 --> 00:54:09.704
Yes.

1068
00:54:09.705 --> 00:54:12.249
Did you drive into it
or away from it?

1069
00:54:15.419 --> 00:54:17.337
It was on the right.

1070
00:54:19.256 --> 00:54:20.923
I don't like you.

1071
00:54:20.924 --> 00:54:22.800
Not required.

1072
00:54:22.801 --> 00:54:24.010
Sun on the right.

1073
00:54:24.011 --> 00:54:26.095
Sun on the right--
they're headed due north.

1074
00:54:26.096 --> 00:54:27.388
possibly northwest.

1075
00:54:27.389 --> 00:54:29.223
Could be on 27. 18
or the interstate.

1076
00:54:29.224 --> 00:54:30.641
Interstate not likely.

1077
00:54:30.642 --> 00:54:32.393
Focus on frontage roads
or county highways.

1078
00:54:32.394 --> 00:54:35.104
Did you pass a street sign?

1079
00:54:35.105 --> 00:54:36.772
JANE:
Yes.

1080
00:54:36.773 --> 00:54:38.441
What did it say?

1081
00:54:38.442 --> 00:54:40.694
(breath continues trembling)

1082
00:54:42.613 --> 00:54:45.823
"Silver Spring: 120 miles."

1083
00:54:45.824 --> 00:54:48.451
Street sign.
"Silver Spring: 120 miles."

1084
00:54:48.452 --> 00:54:51.078
AGENT: I've got half
a dozen towns off the 26.

1085
00:54:51.079 --> 00:54:54.499
Silver Hollow. Oakshade.
Ironmere. Stonemont...

1086
00:54:54.500 --> 00:54:56.459
Try for more details. Jane.

1087
00:54:56.460 --> 00:54:58.211
What else did you pass?

1088
00:54:58.212 --> 00:55:00.004
(breath continues trembling)

1089
00:55:00.005 --> 00:55:01.172
A river.

1090
00:55:01.173 --> 00:55:02.757
Passed a river.

1091
00:55:02.758 --> 00:55:05.010
Did you see a sign for a town
after that?

1092
00:55:07.179 --> 00:55:09.473
- Yes.
- What did it say?

1093
00:55:10.891 --> 00:55:13.893
(whimpering)

1094
00:55:13.894 --> 00:55:15.478
S-Sykesville.

1095
00:55:15.479 --> 00:55:18.482
- Sykesville.
- Sykesville.

1096
00:55:19.399 --> 00:55:21.817
Field is narrowed.
Track and converge.

1097
00:55:21.818 --> 00:55:24.654
Charlie 27. take the lead.
You're four miles out.

1098
00:55:24.655 --> 00:55:26.989
Maintain maximum legal speed.

1099
00:55:26.990 --> 00:55:29.951
How soon after you saw the sign
did you make a turn?

1100
00:55:29.952 --> 00:55:31.744
- A few minutes.
- Few minutes.

1101
00:55:31.745 --> 00:55:33.788
Did you turn right or left?

1102
00:55:33.789 --> 00:55:35.456
- Right.
- Right.

1103
00:55:35.457 --> 00:55:38.251
Do you remember
the name of the road?

1104
00:55:38.252 --> 00:55:39.544
No.

1105
00:55:39.545 --> 00:55:41.672
Do you remember anything
about the road?

1106
00:55:42.673 --> 00:55:44.090
(breath continues trembling)

1107
00:55:44.091 --> 00:55:46.510
(whirring)

1108
00:55:48.262 --> 00:55:50.179
(breath stops trembling)

1109
00:55:50.180 --> 00:55:52.098
It was a dirt road.

1110
00:55:52.099 --> 00:55:53.516
Dirt road.

1111
00:55:53.517 --> 00:55:55.351
Ash Hollow Road.
three and a quarter miles

1112
00:55:55.352 --> 00:55:57.645
outside Sykesville. dead end.

1113
00:55:57.646 --> 00:55:59.313
Farmhouse at the end.

1114
00:55:59.314 --> 00:56:00.856
And found it.

1115
00:56:00.857 --> 00:56:02.191
Ash Hollow Road.

1116
00:56:02.192 --> 00:56:04.570
Target is a farmhouse.

1117
00:56:05.445 --> 00:56:07.781
(tires squealing)

1118
00:56:11.285 --> 00:56:13.578
You've done very well. Jane.

1119
00:56:13.579 --> 00:56:16.122
A service to your country.

1120
00:56:16.123 --> 00:56:19.625
But I have to ask you
one more thing.

1121
00:56:19.626 --> 00:56:23.754
If we can't find Daniel
or we miss him again.

1122
00:56:23.755 --> 00:56:26.382
you may need
to stop him yourself

1123
00:56:26.383 --> 00:56:28.552
any way you can.

1124
00:56:30.512 --> 00:56:33.390
(cries out in pain)

1125
00:56:34.766 --> 00:56:36.851
Hang on. BP just tanked.
88 on 62.

1126
00:56:36.852 --> 00:56:38.811
Uh. heart rate's dropping--
down to 59.

1127
00:56:38.812 --> 00:56:42.064
- Uh. O2 is 93 and falling. 91.
- (Scanlon coughing)

1128
00:56:42.065 --> 00:56:44.901
(breathing deeply)

1129
00:56:46.236 --> 00:56:48.321
92 on 60 and holding.
O2's still dropping. though.

1130
00:56:48.322 --> 00:56:49.572
- Let's start bagging.
- (monitor beeping rapidly)

1131
00:56:49.573 --> 00:56:50.906
Make sure you secure the airway.

1132
00:56:50.907 --> 00:56:53.909
- (air pumping)
- High 80s. Keep going.

1133
00:56:53.910 --> 00:56:55.745
Get away!

1134
00:56:55.746 --> 00:56:57.956
- (breathing heavily)
- (beeping slows)

1135
00:57:01.126 --> 00:57:03.003
Jane.

1136
00:57:03.795 --> 00:57:07.173
What Daniel is trying to do
is wrong.

1137
00:57:07.174 --> 00:57:09.425
It's dangerous.

1138
00:57:09.426 --> 00:57:13.096
It would tip the balance in
an already destabilized world.

1139
00:57:14.097 --> 00:57:15.181
JANE:
Yes.

1140
00:57:15.182 --> 00:57:17.558
Jane. could you stop him
if you had to?

1141
00:57:17.559 --> 00:57:20.604
No. No.

1142
00:57:23.398 --> 00:57:26.400
"Father. if you be willing.

1143
00:57:26.401 --> 00:57:29.445
"let this cup pass me by.

1144
00:57:29.446 --> 00:57:32.782
Yet not as I will.
but as you will."

1145
00:57:32.783 --> 00:57:35.452
And what did Christ say next?

1146
00:57:36.787 --> 00:57:39.331
"By my will.
thine will be done."

1147
00:57:40.123 --> 00:57:43.834
If the moment comes.
I'll be with you.

1148
00:57:43.835 --> 00:57:45.836
and you'll act. Jane.

1149
00:57:45.837 --> 00:57:49.758
out of love for Daniel.
out of love for the human race.

1150
00:57:52.803 --> 00:57:54.763
Now look around the room.

1151
00:57:55.889 --> 00:57:57.182
Slowly.

1152
00:58:00.602 --> 00:58:01.978
Left to right.

1153
00:58:05.148 --> 00:58:06.733
Stop there.

1154
00:58:08.026 --> 00:58:09.653
Get up.

1155
00:58:13.323 --> 00:58:14.490
Walk to the counter.

1156
00:58:14.491 --> 00:58:16.743
♪ ♪

1157
00:58:22.457 --> 00:58:24.543
Pull out the chopping knife.

1158
00:58:31.466 --> 00:58:32.675
Give me your phone!

1159
00:58:32.676 --> 00:58:34.301
- Oh. shit! What?
- Give me your phone.

1160
00:58:34.302 --> 00:58:35.845
Jackson. come on. come on.
come on. give me your phone.

1161
00:58:35.846 --> 00:58:37.012
Give me your phone.
Give me your phone.

1162
00:58:37.013 --> 00:58:38.389
- Okay. hold on. hold on!
- Come on!

1163
00:58:38.390 --> 00:58:39.432
Why? So you can throw it
out the window again?

1164
00:58:39.433 --> 00:58:41.976
(phone ringing)

1165
00:58:41.977 --> 00:58:43.853
Hey. Hugo. why am I
the only one...

1166
00:58:43.854 --> 00:58:46.397
- Daniel Kellner.
- Oh. my God. Daniel Kellner.

1167
00:58:46.398 --> 00:58:48.065
MARGARET (over phone):
They know where you are.

1168
00:58:48.066 --> 00:58:49.608
They know. Do you understand?

1169
00:58:49.609 --> 00:58:50.693
Who is this?

1170
00:58:50.694 --> 00:58:52.445
Do not go back to the house.

1171
00:58:52.446 --> 00:58:54.739
Scan-Scanlon dove on Jane.

1172
00:58:54.740 --> 00:58:56.198
Does that mean anything to you?

1173
00:58:56.199 --> 00:58:58.033
- Okay. Give me your...
- Look. they found you.

1174
00:58:58.034 --> 00:58:59.952
I don't know who you are.
and I don't know who they are.

1175
00:58:59.953 --> 00:59:01.495
but they're gonna kill you.

1176
00:59:01.496 --> 00:59:03.038
- Give me the phone.
- They are gonna kill you both.

1177
00:59:03.039 --> 00:59:04.582
- Give me my phone!
- You need to leave.

1178
00:59:04.583 --> 00:59:06.125
Give me my phone. Maggie!
Give me my phone! Oh. my God!

1179
00:59:06.126 --> 00:59:08.252
I'm so done
with your crazy shit!

1180
00:59:08.253 --> 00:59:09.880
(line clicks)

1181
00:59:15.302 --> 00:59:17.554
(panting)

1182
00:59:20.223 --> 00:59:22.225
(vehicles approaching)

1183
00:59:32.402 --> 00:59:34.654
(Daniel breathing heavily)

1184
00:59:42.454 --> 00:59:44.331
(softly):
Okay. Okay.

1185
00:59:52.088 --> 00:59:55.008
(birds chirping)

1186
01:00:02.015 --> 01:00:04.059
(panting)

1187
01:00:22.577 --> 01:00:24.328
(vehicle door opens)

1188
01:00:24.329 --> 01:00:25.997
(grunts)

1189
01:00:27.374 --> 01:00:29.251
(vehicle door closes)

1190
01:00:44.766 --> 01:00:46.977
(indistinct chatter)

1191
01:00:49.187 --> 01:00:50.856
(car door opens)

1192
01:00:59.239 --> 01:01:00.824
Okay.

1193
01:01:02.659 --> 01:01:04.159
(engine starts)

1194
01:01:04.160 --> 01:01:08.497
What am I doing?
What am I doing? Okay.

1195
01:01:08.498 --> 01:01:09.832
What am I doing?
What am I doing?

1196
01:01:09.833 --> 01:01:11.500
- What am I doing?
What am I doing? -Hold it!

1197
01:01:11.501 --> 01:01:13.335
- What am I doing? What am I
doing? What am I doing? -Stop!

1198
01:01:13.336 --> 01:01:14.712
- Hey! He's in the car! -Watch
out. watch out. watch out!

1199
01:01:14.713 --> 01:01:17.381
- What am I doing?
- (engine revving)

1200
01:01:17.382 --> 01:01:19.049
AGENT:
Shoot the tires!

1201
01:01:19.050 --> 01:01:20.509
It's him! It's him!

1202
01:01:20.510 --> 01:01:21.886
Watch out!

1203
01:01:21.887 --> 01:01:23.804
(indistinct shouting)

1204
01:01:23.805 --> 01:01:26.349
(gunfire)

1205
01:01:27.183 --> 01:01:29.102
AGENT:
Go for the tires!

1206
01:01:30.854 --> 01:01:33.857
(panting)

1207
01:01:35.275 --> 01:01:36.985
Oh. shit.

1208
01:01:37.777 --> 01:01:40.238
(engines revving in distance)

1209
01:01:48.288 --> 01:01:50.415
(tires squealing)

1210
01:01:53.919 --> 01:01:57.880
What am I doing?
What am I doing? What am I...

1211
01:01:57.881 --> 01:01:59.883
What am I doing?

1212
01:02:03.887 --> 01:02:05.304
- Hands up!
- Stop!

1213
01:02:05.305 --> 01:02:06.472
Get him!

1214
01:02:06.473 --> 01:02:07.723
Get out! Now!

1215
01:02:07.724 --> 01:02:08.766
- Get out of the car!
- (engine revving)

1216
01:02:08.767 --> 01:02:10.184
Let me see your hands! Hands up!

1217
01:02:10.185 --> 01:02:12.103
- Hands up!
- (tires squealing)

1218
01:02:24.616 --> 01:02:26.868
♪ ♪

1219
01:02:28.620 --> 01:02:30.872
(breathing heavily)

1220
01:02:42.425 --> 01:02:44.803
(engines revving)

1221
01:02:45.512 --> 01:02:47.222
(Daniel grunts)

1222
01:02:48.556 --> 01:02:50.141
Get your seat belt on!

1223
01:03:00.735 --> 01:03:01.945
Jane!

1224
01:03:02.779 --> 01:03:04.239
Jane.

1225
01:03:05.490 --> 01:03:07.117
(engines revving)

1226
01:03:14.624 --> 01:03:17.419
(breathing heavily)

1227
01:03:19.671 --> 01:03:20.796
(whimpering)

1228
01:03:20.797 --> 01:03:22.423
(heavy. shaky breathing)

1229
01:03:22.424 --> 01:03:23.841
(straining)

1230
01:03:23.842 --> 01:03:24.883
(grunts)

1231
01:03:24.884 --> 01:03:27.303
(whimpering. straining)

1232
01:03:29.139 --> 01:03:31.598
- (screams)
- (cries out in pain)

1233
01:03:31.599 --> 01:03:33.684
(breathing heavily)

1234
01:03:33.685 --> 01:03:36.020
(indistinct chatter)

1235
01:03:36.021 --> 01:03:37.980
- He's seizing. Stretch him out.
- Watch his head.

1236
01:03:37.981 --> 01:03:39.398
- Watch his head.
- I need a bite block.

1237
01:03:39.399 --> 01:03:41.443
♪ ♪

1238
01:03:46.197 --> 01:03:47.323
(grunts)

1239
01:03:50.994 --> 01:03:52.536
(gun fires)

1240
01:03:52.537 --> 01:03:53.830
Get down!

1241
01:03:58.668 --> 01:04:00.669
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa!

1242
01:04:00.670 --> 01:04:02.004
(tires squealing)

1243
01:04:02.005 --> 01:04:03.256
(gasps)

1244
01:04:08.386 --> 01:04:11.096
No. no. no. no. no. no.
no. no. no. no. no.

1245
01:04:11.097 --> 01:04:12.514
No. no. no. no. no.

1246
01:04:12.515 --> 01:04:14.683
Look. Jane. it wasn't you.
It wasn't you.

1247
01:04:14.684 --> 01:04:15.976
It was Scanlon.

1248
01:04:15.977 --> 01:04:17.311
The device. The device.

1249
01:04:17.312 --> 01:04:19.939
Roll him on three.
One. two. three. go.

1250
01:04:25.195 --> 01:04:27.113
What the hell just happened?

1251
01:04:32.494 --> 01:04:33.994
- Secure the device!
- I got it. I got it.

1252
01:04:33.995 --> 01:04:35.330
I'm gloved. I'm gloved.

1253
01:04:42.504 --> 01:04:44.464
(tires squeal)

1254
01:04:48.426 --> 01:04:50.887
(engine revving)

1255
01:04:52.722 --> 01:04:55.058
Look behind us!
Tell me what you see!

1256
01:05:01.397 --> 01:05:04.109
Dust. I see dust.

1257
01:05:05.360 --> 01:05:07.904
They're coming! They're coming!

1258
01:05:08.780 --> 01:05:10.781
Stop. stop. stop. stop!

1259
01:05:10.782 --> 01:05:12.825
(tires squealing)

1260
01:05:12.826 --> 01:05:15.203
(rocks clattering)

1261
01:05:19.666 --> 01:05:21.584
(panting)

1262
01:05:32.512 --> 01:05:34.013
Run!

1263
01:05:34.806 --> 01:05:36.349
JANE:
Wait!

1264
01:05:37.600 --> 01:05:40.311
- What are you doing?
- Put it in drive!

1265
01:06:00.206 --> 01:06:02.332
(urgent chatter)

1266
01:06:02.333 --> 01:06:04.293
- You see them?
- You got a visual?

1267
01:06:04.294 --> 01:06:05.794
- Anybody got eyes on anything?
- They must have gone over.

1268
01:06:05.795 --> 01:06:07.462
Requesting underwater search
and recovery

1269
01:06:07.463 --> 01:06:08.964
- on site right now.
- They're down. They're down.

1270
01:06:08.965 --> 01:06:10.632
They're down.
They're in the water.

1271
01:06:10.633 --> 01:06:12.092
Can we get a team down there
and see if we can find them?

1272
01:06:12.093 --> 01:06:13.719
- We need some divers.
- Down there.

1273
01:06:13.720 --> 01:06:15.929
(chatter continues indistinctly)

1274
01:06:15.930 --> 01:06:18.015
(horns honking)

1275
01:06:18.016 --> 01:06:20.268
(panicked chatter)

1276
01:06:36.701 --> 01:06:38.493
They all think
the world's going to hell.

1277
01:06:38.494 --> 01:06:40.162
Got to get going now.
Jackson. okay?

1278
01:06:40.163 --> 01:06:41.413
Daniel Kellner's gonna be there.

1279
01:06:41.414 --> 01:06:42.915
Not right now.
but he will be soon.

1280
01:06:42.916 --> 01:06:44.583
- We got to go north.
- No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

1281
01:06:44.584 --> 01:06:46.376
- Got to go north right now.
- No. we need to...

1282
01:06:46.377 --> 01:06:47.920
- We need to go back to the
hospital. -No. no. no. Jack.

1283
01:06:47.921 --> 01:06:49.463
This is not something you
get treated for. It's not...

1284
01:06:49.464 --> 01:06:50.881
You know what's wrong with you.

1285
01:06:50.882 --> 01:06:52.966
is that you think there's
something wrong with me.

1286
01:06:52.967 --> 01:06:55.053
Look at me. Look at me.

1287
01:06:56.804 --> 01:06:58.681
If I moved. you'd stay.

1288
01:06:59.807 --> 01:07:01.183
- What?
- Kansas City.

1289
01:07:01.184 --> 01:07:03.478
You want me to move.
You're gonna stay.

1290
01:07:23.581 --> 01:07:24.873
(sighs)

1291
01:07:24.874 --> 01:07:27.960
You know. this thing
that's happening. it's...

1292
01:07:27.961 --> 01:07:29.836
(takes deep breath)

1293
01:07:29.837 --> 01:07:31.171
It's not coming from me.

1294
01:07:31.172 --> 01:07:33.882
It's like I'm just a passenger.

1295
01:07:33.883 --> 01:07:35.300
That's not a bad thing.

1296
01:07:35.301 --> 01:07:37.804
It's. like. a really good thing.

1297
01:07:38.596 --> 01:07:40.597
- It's like your music.
- Uh-huh.

1298
01:07:40.598 --> 01:07:43.100
You know when you're
in the flow?

1299
01:07:43.101 --> 01:07:45.395
And it just feels...

1300
01:07:47.105 --> 01:07:48.981
I'm in the flow.

1301
01:07:48.982 --> 01:07:50.107
Okay.

1302
01:07:50.108 --> 01:07:51.441
And I told you I'd tell you

1303
01:07:51.442 --> 01:07:54.987
when I get where
I'm supposed to be. and...

1304
01:07:54.988 --> 01:07:56.571
this is it.

1305
01:07:56.572 --> 01:07:58.573
- Okay.
- Right here.

1306
01:07:58.574 --> 01:08:01.660
- It's where I'm supposed to be.
- Okay.

1307
01:08:01.661 --> 01:08:04.246
S-So...

1308
01:08:04.247 --> 01:08:09.418
we need to go north because
that's where Daniel Kellner is?

1309
01:08:09.419 --> 01:08:11.461
Sorry. No. He's east.

1310
01:08:11.462 --> 01:08:13.171
- Oh. And...
- He's east now.

1311
01:08:13.172 --> 01:08:14.756
How do you know that it's east?

1312
01:08:14.757 --> 01:08:18.218
It's just. I have
this vague inclination.

1313
01:08:18.219 --> 01:08:19.970
But he's east now.
He's somewhere east.

1314
01:08:19.971 --> 01:08:22.682
And where is "somewhere"?

1315
01:08:24.392 --> 01:08:26.436
You want me to drive?

1316
01:08:27.937 --> 01:08:29.647
I need a water.

1317
01:08:36.487 --> 01:08:38.281
(entry bell jingling)

1318
01:08:43.161 --> 01:08:44.703
Hey.

1319
01:08:44.704 --> 01:08:46.581
Hello. Hi.

1320
01:08:47.540 --> 01:08:49.625
Hi. Um...

1321
01:08:51.836 --> 01:08:53.337
Will you do me a favor?

1322
01:08:53.338 --> 01:08:55.005
- Dr. Coleman?
- (lively chatter)

1323
01:08:55.006 --> 01:08:57.341
Uh. uh. yes. yes. Thank you.
thank you for taking the call.

1324
01:08:57.342 --> 01:08:59.134
Uh. I-I don't know.

1325
01:08:59.135 --> 01:09:03.221
She just took off. and y-y-yes.
it's getting worse. much worse.

1326
01:09:03.222 --> 01:09:04.514
Yes. please. Thank you.

1327
01:09:04.515 --> 01:09:05.932
Yes. Hold on one second.

1328
01:09:05.933 --> 01:09:07.225
Excuse me. sir.

1329
01:09:07.226 --> 01:09:08.810
Do you know the address
around here?

1330
01:09:08.811 --> 01:09:11.147
37 Pearl Street. Decatur.

1331
01:09:11.898 --> 01:09:15.025
37 Pearl Street. Decatur.

1332
01:09:15.026 --> 01:09:16.943
We'll be here. Thank you.

1333
01:09:16.944 --> 01:09:18.488
(entry bell jingling)

1334
01:09:27.538 --> 01:09:29.332
BOY:
Hey. mister.

1335
01:09:30.166 --> 01:09:34.337
She said to say she loves you.
but she's going east.

1336
01:09:50.186 --> 01:09:51.686
Why Kansas City?

1337
01:09:51.687 --> 01:09:55.065
Best to focus on
getting you there tomorrow.

1338
01:09:55.066 --> 01:09:57.610
DANIEL (panting):
Hugo. I'm...

1339
01:09:59.237 --> 01:10:01.029
Uh. it's coming back to me.

1340
01:10:01.030 --> 01:10:02.989
Things are coming back to me.

1341
01:10:02.990 --> 01:10:04.324
What things?

1342
01:10:04.325 --> 01:10:05.992
Animals.

1343
01:10:05.993 --> 01:10:09.539
Friendly. terrifying animals
looking at me.

1344
01:10:10.915 --> 01:10:14.042
And you can't look away
no matter how hard you try?

1345
01:10:14.043 --> 01:10:16.879
No. no.
They have to look away first.

1346
01:10:19.549 --> 01:10:22.427
Is this a memory or a dream?

1347
01:10:23.219 --> 01:10:25.053
I can't tell anymore.

1348
01:10:25.054 --> 01:10:27.390
(shower water running)

1349
01:10:29.225 --> 01:10:30.893
HUGO:
Daniel?

1350
01:10:32.979 --> 01:10:34.564
Daniel.

1351
01:10:35.398 --> 01:10:36.773
Daniel.

1352
01:10:36.774 --> 01:10:39.025
It wasn't your idea
to recruit me. was it?

1353
01:10:39.026 --> 01:10:42.697
Not just for this but-but
to WARDEX in the first place.

1354
01:10:45.241 --> 01:10:46.950
No. it wasn't.

1355
01:10:46.951 --> 01:10:49.369
And there was a reason?

1356
01:10:49.370 --> 01:10:51.747
A specific reason
why you wanted me?

1357
01:10:52.999 --> 01:10:56.711
Other than your prodigious gift
for numbers? Yes.

1358
01:10:57.545 --> 01:11:00.464
You decided to keep
all of this to yourself?

1359
01:11:00.465 --> 01:11:03.592
Because I care about you.

1360
01:11:03.593 --> 01:11:05.510
Because you have a job to do.

1361
01:11:05.511 --> 01:11:09.348
And nothing can get
in the way of that.

1362
01:11:11.934 --> 01:11:13.978
There's parts of me...

1363
01:11:15.771 --> 01:11:19.232
...from when I was a kid
that I should be able to know.

1364
01:11:19.233 --> 01:11:20.943
and I don't.

1365
01:11:24.405 --> 01:11:26.282
They're just gone.

1366
01:11:27.033 --> 01:11:29.285
I'm so scared.

1367
01:11:30.286 --> 01:11:32.370
You don't need to be.

1368
01:11:32.371 --> 01:11:35.081
You have me and someone else.

1369
01:11:35.082 --> 01:11:39.044
And when the time is right.
everything will become clear.

1370
01:11:39.045 --> 01:11:41.796
Daniel. there's a place
you'll need to be

1371
01:11:41.797 --> 01:11:43.882
in the morning without fail.

1372
01:11:43.883 --> 01:11:46.886
There will be no other day
like tomorrow.

1373
01:11:49.597 --> 01:11:52.308
Where do you need me to go?

1374
01:11:54.310 --> 01:11:56.436
KCXE?

1375
01:11:56.437 --> 01:11:58.481
What's KCXE?

1376
01:12:38.896 --> 01:12:41.064
Danny. I'm gonna ask you
to do something.

1377
01:12:41.065 --> 01:12:42.899
(Margaret speaking indistinctly
on video)

1378
01:12:42.900 --> 01:12:45.069
I want you first
to look at this.

1379
01:12:45.861 --> 01:12:48.531
(Margaret speaking
unintelligibly on video)

1380
01:12:49.532 --> 01:12:51.450
Do you understand
what she's saying?

1381
01:12:52.410 --> 01:12:54.369
I hear her. It-it's gibberish.

1382
01:12:54.370 --> 01:12:55.870
I can't understand it.

1383
01:12:55.871 --> 01:12:59.958
Okay. I-I just heard this
for the first time.

1384
01:12:59.959 --> 01:13:01.293
and I can.

1385
01:13:01.294 --> 01:13:02.794
- It's English.
- English?

1386
01:13:02.795 --> 01:13:05.171
I mean. it's-it's math
turned English in my head.

1387
01:13:05.172 --> 01:13:06.882
translated into words.

1388
01:13:07.633 --> 01:13:11.011
When I look at this.
I hear this.

1389
01:13:11.012 --> 01:13:14.390
(Margaret clicking tongue
on video)

1390
01:13:15.558 --> 01:13:18.019
Danny. I'm gonna ask you
to do something.

1391
01:13:26.861 --> 01:13:28.779
You can't trust me anymore.

1392
01:13:31.907 --> 01:13:34.118
- (insects chirping)
- (sign creaking)

1393
01:13:47.590 --> 01:13:49.091
(gasps softly)

1394
01:13:50.593 --> 01:13:52.177
(hisses in pain)

1395
01:13:52.178 --> 01:13:54.429
(sighs)

1396
01:13:54.430 --> 01:13:56.557
(whimpers)

1397
01:14:02.480 --> 01:14:04.732
♪ ♪

1398
01:14:24.293 --> 01:14:26.545
♪ ♪

1399
01:14:40.851 --> 01:14:43.103
- (breathing heavily)
- (monitor beeping steadily)

1400
01:14:43.104 --> 01:14:44.897
Got him.

1401
01:14:47.149 --> 01:14:49.110
(groans)

1402
01:14:53.489 --> 01:14:55.741
(engine revving)

1403
01:15:13.134 --> 01:15:15.636
(engines revving)

1404
01:15:23.686 --> 01:15:25.771
(tires squealing)

1405
01:15:26.772 --> 01:15:29.024
(Daniel gasping)

1406
01:15:31.360 --> 01:15:33.904
(urgent chatter)

1407
01:15:36.449 --> 01:15:37.866
- They're here.
- (gasps)

1408
01:15:37.867 --> 01:15:39.409
- They're here.
- What?

1409
01:15:39.410 --> 01:15:41.661
- Take that end.
- Go. go. go.

1410
01:15:41.662 --> 01:15:43.873
(panting)

1411
01:15:44.957 --> 01:15:47.877
- The backpack. The backpack!
- You first.

1412
01:15:51.255 --> 01:15:53.299
(urgent chatter continues)

1413
01:16:00.347 --> 01:16:01.514
Come on.

1414
01:16:01.515 --> 01:16:03.808
This is all I've got.

1415
01:16:03.809 --> 01:16:05.393
You're coming. right?

1416
01:16:05.394 --> 01:16:06.811
- (banging at door)
- Shit.

1417
01:16:06.812 --> 01:16:08.063
Breach! Here!

1418
01:16:09.064 --> 01:16:10.523
(urgent chatter)

1419
01:16:10.524 --> 01:16:11.858
- No. come on. come on. come on.
- You got to take this.

1420
01:16:11.859 --> 01:16:13.485
(urgent chatter continues)

1421
01:16:13.486 --> 01:16:17.030
And for God's sake. Jane.
don't touch what's inside.

1422
01:16:17.031 --> 01:16:17.906
Go. Go.

1423
01:16:17.907 --> 01:16:20.117
(urgent chatter continues)

1424
01:16:23.829 --> 01:16:26.582
- (grunting)
- Get out of there!

1425
01:16:32.755 --> 01:16:34.715
Get on the ground!

1426
01:16:37.384 --> 01:16:39.053
They're burned.

1427
01:16:41.680 --> 01:16:43.264
(breathing heavily)

1428
01:16:43.265 --> 01:16:45.684
(agents shouting indistinctly
in distance)

1429
01:16:55.277 --> 01:16:56.946
It's not here.

1430
01:17:01.659 --> 01:17:03.285
Where's the device?

1431
01:17:08.457 --> 01:17:09.958
(sighs)

1432
01:17:09.959 --> 01:17:12.169
(jet engine whirring)

1433
01:17:19.844 --> 01:17:22.096
♪ ♪

1434
01:17:44.243 --> 01:17:45.827
SCANLON:
You've been misled. Daniel.

1435
01:17:45.828 --> 01:17:48.663
We can talk another time
about how hurtful

1436
01:17:48.664 --> 01:17:50.290
all this has been to me.

1437
01:17:50.291 --> 01:17:52.834
but here we are.

1438
01:17:52.835 --> 01:17:54.419
The archive's safe.

1439
01:17:54.420 --> 01:17:56.963
And now you're going
to tell me the name

1440
01:17:56.964 --> 01:17:58.882
of every confederate at WARDEX

1441
01:17:58.883 --> 01:18:01.510
and what exactly
Hugo's operation is planning.

1442
01:18:02.344 --> 01:18:05.764
But first.
without all this nonsense...

1443
01:18:08.309 --> 01:18:11.270
...you're going to tell me
what you did with the device.

1444
01:18:14.440 --> 01:18:16.817
(tires squealing)

1445
01:18:17.610 --> 01:18:19.862
♪ ♪

1446
01:18:30.497 --> 01:18:32.124
(tires squeal)

1447
01:18:34.209 --> 01:18:36.711
The hell do you think
you're doing driving like that?

1448
01:18:36.712 --> 01:18:39.130
You are Agent Thomas Farley.

1449
01:18:39.131 --> 01:18:42.592
Your ten-digit I.D. code is
3893398887.

1450
01:18:42.593 --> 01:18:44.762
What's the day code?

1451
01:18:45.721 --> 01:18:47.431
Kentucky filly.

1452
01:18:49.892 --> 01:18:52.019
(tires squealing)

1453
01:19:02.112 --> 01:19:03.863
- Agent Grady?
- Yes. ma'am.

1454
01:19:03.864 --> 01:19:05.615
Kentucky filly.
Mr. Scanlon sent for me.

1455
01:19:05.616 --> 01:19:07.076
Follow me.

1456
01:19:10.871 --> 01:19:12.747
(engine shuts off)

1457
01:19:12.748 --> 01:19:14.959
♪ ♪

1458
01:19:33.560 --> 01:19:35.771
♪ ♪

1459
01:19:51.996 --> 01:19:53.455
You're her.

1460
01:19:59.795 --> 01:20:02.256
Margaret Fairchild.

1461
01:20:21.650 --> 01:20:23.277
Jocelyn.

1462
01:20:28.949 --> 01:20:30.492
Jocelyn.

1463
01:20:37.666 --> 01:20:39.333
(gasps)

1464
01:20:39.334 --> 01:20:40.668
(grunting)

1465
01:20:40.669 --> 01:20:41.836
Leave her!

1466
01:20:41.837 --> 01:20:43.422
Stand down.

1467
01:21:01.440 --> 01:21:03.859
I know you.

1468
01:21:14.578 --> 01:21:16.913
I know you. too.

1469
01:21:16.914 --> 01:21:18.873
There's two coming out.

1470
01:21:18.874 --> 01:21:20.584
Don't allow them off the base.

1471
01:21:23.837 --> 01:21:26.380
Hey. Hey. Hey. back inside.

1472
01:21:26.381 --> 01:21:28.174
MARGARET: I've waited
too long to tell you.

1473
01:21:28.175 --> 01:21:29.968
and now it's too late.

1474
01:21:30.886 --> 01:21:33.972
But I loved you like my own son.

1475
01:21:37.059 --> 01:21:39.394
Stop. Stop. Stop.

1476
01:21:40.187 --> 01:21:41.729
They said we could go up
to the lake on Friday.

1477
01:21:41.730 --> 01:21:43.731
and-and Grandma and Grandpa
will be there.

1478
01:21:43.732 --> 01:21:48.402
and-and Uncle Howard and Bobby
and Teresa and everybody.

1479
01:21:48.403 --> 01:21:50.447
♪ ♪

1480
01:22:00.249 --> 01:22:02.083
How do you know these people?

1481
01:22:02.084 --> 01:22:03.751
MARGARET:
I don't.

1482
01:22:03.752 --> 01:22:05.587
You were just talking to them.

1483
01:22:11.176 --> 01:22:12.885
I don't understand
what's happening.

1484
01:22:12.886 --> 01:22:14.680
MARGARET:
Just get in!

1485
01:22:20.978 --> 01:22:23.564
- What did you see?
- (engine starts)

1486
01:22:24.648 --> 01:22:26.567
My wife.

1487
01:22:30.863 --> 01:22:32.614
My God.

1488
01:22:33.615 --> 01:22:35.284
What is she?

1489
01:22:36.618 --> 01:22:38.452
Unstoppable.

1490
01:22:38.453 --> 01:22:40.622
♪ ♪

1491
01:22:43.375 --> 01:22:44.960
(beeping)

1492
01:22:49.923 --> 01:22:51.340
DANIEL:
Where are you taking us?

1493
01:22:51.341 --> 01:22:53.301
MARGARET:
Kansas City.

1494
01:22:53.302 --> 01:22:54.677
DANIEL:
Why there?

1495
01:22:54.678 --> 01:22:56.637
- I have to.
- You don't have to go so...

1496
01:22:56.638 --> 01:22:58.681
- Yeah. uh. yeah. I do.
- Uh. you're enjoying this.

1497
01:22:58.682 --> 01:23:01.434
Yeah. I mean. it-it feels good.
It feels good. and then...

1498
01:23:01.435 --> 01:23:03.477
Yeah. but-but... but you know.
You know.

1499
01:23:03.478 --> 01:23:05.188
I mean. you've been driving
like a maniac

1500
01:23:05.189 --> 01:23:06.606
the last few days. you know.

1501
01:23:06.607 --> 01:23:08.482
- How do you know that?
- I just know things.

1502
01:23:08.483 --> 01:23:10.151
It's just. something happened
to me a couple of days ago.

1503
01:23:10.152 --> 01:23:12.195
and now I-I know things.

1504
01:23:12.196 --> 01:23:13.487
Things I don't really
want to know.

1505
01:23:13.488 --> 01:23:14.906
and all the things
I do want to know.

1506
01:23:14.907 --> 01:23:16.157
I don't really know at all.

1507
01:23:16.158 --> 01:23:17.533
so I've just been
kind of rolling with it.

1508
01:23:17.534 --> 01:23:19.410
You know. like...
Oh. wow. you were in jail?

1509
01:23:19.411 --> 01:23:20.953
- That must have been so...
- Hey. hey!

1510
01:23:20.954 --> 01:23:22.955
- (tires squealing)
- MARGARET: You see what I mean?

1511
01:23:22.956 --> 01:23:24.957
It's crazy. It's crazy.

1512
01:23:24.958 --> 01:23:29.004
I look at somebody.
and I just drop in on them.

1513
01:23:29.755 --> 01:23:32.590
It's like. for a few seconds.
I am them.

1514
01:23:32.591 --> 01:23:34.383
I see the things
that they've lived.

1515
01:23:34.384 --> 01:23:36.677
It's just like
it's all happening to me. too.

1516
01:23:36.678 --> 01:23:37.887
You know. like-like...

1517
01:23:37.888 --> 01:23:39.513
like right now
your shoulder's killing you.

1518
01:23:39.514 --> 01:23:41.390
Yeah. and you-you just
want to yell.

1519
01:23:41.391 --> 01:23:42.850
- "Keep your eyes on the road!"
- Keep your eyes on the road!

1520
01:23:42.851 --> 01:23:44.644
I know. and you can't stop
thinking about Jane.

1521
01:23:44.645 --> 01:23:46.020
and Jane should be back
at the Monastery St. Clare.

1522
01:23:46.021 --> 01:23:47.396
- You're absolutely right.
- Jane?

1523
01:23:47.397 --> 01:23:50.191
But then yesterday.
I'm driving with Jackson.

1524
01:23:50.192 --> 01:23:52.235
and I flashed on you
without seeing you.

1525
01:23:52.236 --> 01:23:53.903
(makes whooshing sound)
It was so strong.

1526
01:23:53.904 --> 01:23:55.404
I dropped right in on you

1527
01:23:55.405 --> 01:23:56.948
without even needing
to look at you. and that was

1528
01:23:56.949 --> 01:23:59.033
the first time that crazy shit
has ever happened to me.

1529
01:23:59.034 --> 01:24:00.743
How long you been able
to do this?

1530
01:24:00.744 --> 01:24:01.994
Since yesterday.

1531
01:24:01.995 --> 01:24:03.579
Since the bird.

1532
01:24:03.580 --> 01:24:05.248
- What bird?
- This-this bird.

1533
01:24:05.249 --> 01:24:06.791
Flew in through my window.

1534
01:24:06.792 --> 01:24:08.960
It was beautiful. I looked
at it. and then it-it...

1535
01:24:08.961 --> 01:24:10.044
Was it a cardinal?

1536
01:24:10.045 --> 01:24:11.337
Holy sh... How the...

1537
01:24:11.338 --> 01:24:12.713
You're freaking me the fuck out.

1538
01:24:12.714 --> 01:24:16.051
- (tires squealing)
- (crossing bell dinging)

1539
01:24:18.929 --> 01:24:20.304
I was 20. I was in college.

1540
01:24:20.305 --> 01:24:22.265
You were flunking out.
basically. right?

1541
01:24:22.266 --> 01:24:23.599
Yeah. I-I was pretty smart.

1542
01:24:23.600 --> 01:24:25.142
You were. but it was
the partying.

1543
01:24:25.143 --> 01:24:26.227
It was the partying
and the drugs.

1544
01:24:26.228 --> 01:24:27.687
I mean. ketamine? Come on. dude.

1545
01:24:27.688 --> 01:24:29.146
- Could you please stop?
- Sorry. I'm stopping.

1546
01:24:29.147 --> 01:24:30.398
- I was 20. I was in college.
- Yes.

1547
01:24:30.399 --> 01:24:32.984
Uh. it was dark. I-I was in bed.

1548
01:24:32.985 --> 01:24:35.486
and I dreamed that
something was watching me.

1549
01:24:35.487 --> 01:24:37.196
I woke up.
and there was this bird.

1550
01:24:37.197 --> 01:24:38.572
- It was a cardinal.
- In the window.

1551
01:24:38.573 --> 01:24:40.700
and it-it looked at me.
and after that.

1552
01:24:40.701 --> 01:24:41.993
everything just changed.

1553
01:24:41.994 --> 01:24:44.745
I saw things:
context. patterns. artifacting.

1554
01:24:44.746 --> 01:24:46.163
I could see it all.

1555
01:24:46.164 --> 01:24:48.249
Arrays and conditionals
just appeared in my head...

1556
01:24:48.250 --> 01:24:49.875
Fully solved. "If P. then Q."

1557
01:24:49.876 --> 01:24:51.252
Exactly. Solved equations

1558
01:24:51.253 --> 01:24:52.670
- without even thinking...
- And you could read

1559
01:24:52.671 --> 01:24:54.171
eight-bit binary data
like it was English.

1560
01:24:54.172 --> 01:24:55.298
- like it was nothing.
- Yeah.

1561
01:24:55.299 --> 01:24:56.590
How do you know all this?

1562
01:24:56.591 --> 01:24:58.134
I don't. You do.

1563
01:24:58.135 --> 01:24:59.343
God. you hated it.

1564
01:24:59.344 --> 01:25:01.178
- It was a curse.
- Yeah.

1565
01:25:01.179 --> 01:25:02.805
I couldn't relate to anybody.

1566
01:25:02.806 --> 01:25:04.682
I lost every friend I ever had
because I-I couldn't stand

1567
01:25:04.683 --> 01:25:06.434
- to be around people.
- (train horn blaring)

1568
01:25:06.435 --> 01:25:08.312
Until you met Jane.

1569
01:25:09.438 --> 01:25:11.522
- (train horn continues blaring)
- (bell clanging)

1570
01:25:11.523 --> 01:25:13.274
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know."

1571
01:25:13.275 --> 01:25:15.067
- What?
- That's what you said on TV.

1572
01:25:15.068 --> 01:25:16.736
They said I was
talking nonsense.

1573
01:25:16.737 --> 01:25:18.070
I understood every word.

1574
01:25:18.071 --> 01:25:19.697
What happened to us?

1575
01:25:19.698 --> 01:25:21.699
- (Daniel grunts)
- (gasps) Oh. my God.

1576
01:25:21.700 --> 01:25:23.951
- (tires squealing)
- (both grunting)

1577
01:25:23.952 --> 01:25:25.412
Who is it?!

1578
01:25:27.956 --> 01:25:29.165
Boyd. stop!

1579
01:25:29.166 --> 01:25:30.459
Boyd!

1580
01:25:32.753 --> 01:25:34.795
(engine revving)

1581
01:25:34.796 --> 01:25:36.590
(grunts)

1582
01:25:39.676 --> 01:25:40.719
Shit.

1583
01:25:41.553 --> 01:25:43.346
We got to jump! We got to bail!

1584
01:25:43.347 --> 01:25:45.432
I can't!
I'm standing on the brakes!

1585
01:25:49.311 --> 01:25:51.396
Oh. my God! Oh. my God!

1586
01:25:53.315 --> 01:25:54.649
No. no. no. no. no. no. no!

1587
01:25:56.985 --> 01:25:58.653
He's backing up! Get out now!

1588
01:26:09.039 --> 01:26:11.083
(both grunting)

1589
01:26:12.000 --> 01:26:14.211
- (Margaret screaming)
- All right. all right!

1590
01:26:22.469 --> 01:26:24.221
Get to the ladder!

1591
01:26:29.810 --> 01:26:32.019
MARGARET:
Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1592
01:26:32.020 --> 01:26:33.396
DANIEL:
Okay.

1593
01:26:33.397 --> 01:26:35.357
(train horn blasting
in distance)

1594
01:26:39.403 --> 01:26:41.362
(horn continues blasting)

1595
01:26:41.363 --> 01:26:43.782
(both grunting)

1596
01:26:52.624 --> 01:26:55.210
- (bullets ricocheting)
- (grunting)

1597
01:26:57.587 --> 01:26:59.463
(gasping. whimpering)

1598
01:26:59.464 --> 01:27:01.800
- (horn honking)
- (tires squealing)

1599
01:27:08.056 --> 01:27:09.223
(train horn blaring)

1600
01:27:09.224 --> 01:27:11.308
Go! Jump!

1601
01:27:11.309 --> 01:27:13.395
(metallic creaking)

1602
01:27:14.855 --> 01:27:16.690
(gasps)

1603
01:27:19.151 --> 01:27:21.736
(horn blasting)

1604
01:27:24.156 --> 01:27:25.907
You got to jump!

1605
01:27:26.908 --> 01:27:28.493
Jump! Now!

1606
01:27:33.498 --> 01:27:36.543
- (Daniel straining)
- (breathing heavily)

1607
01:27:38.295 --> 01:27:40.255
(muffled shouting)

1608
01:27:50.348 --> 01:27:52.934
(grunting)

1609
01:27:54.603 --> 01:27:57.272
(heavy. gasping breaths)

1610
01:28:02.986 --> 01:28:04.529
Oh. my God.

1611
01:28:08.158 --> 01:28:11.495
(piano strings resonating)

1612
01:28:12.412 --> 01:28:15.457
I can't breathe.
I can't breathe.

1613
01:28:16.208 --> 01:28:17.709
I can't breathe.

1614
01:28:18.793 --> 01:28:21.045
- It's okay. It's okay.
- I can't breathe.

1615
01:28:21.046 --> 01:28:22.796
- I think you're having
a panic attack. -Oh. my God.

1616
01:28:22.797 --> 01:28:24.965
- It's okay. It's okay.
- Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1617
01:28:24.966 --> 01:28:26.842
- It's okay. I'm used to 'em.
- (stammers) My hands.

1618
01:28:26.843 --> 01:28:28.677
- We're okay.
- It's like my dad.

1619
01:28:28.678 --> 01:28:30.137
- It's like my dad. My hands.
- No. no. no. No. no. no. no.

1620
01:28:30.138 --> 01:28:32.348
It's like Parkinson's.
It's like Parkinson's.

1621
01:28:32.349 --> 01:28:33.641
It's not the same thing.
It's not that.

1622
01:28:33.642 --> 01:28:35.142
Yes. it is. It's the same.

1623
01:28:35.143 --> 01:28:37.311
No. he couldn't control it.
I can't control it.

1624
01:28:37.312 --> 01:28:38.812
- I can't control it.
- You can.

1625
01:28:38.813 --> 01:28:41.398
(sobbing): Oh. my God.
I ran away from him.

1626
01:28:41.399 --> 01:28:44.485
- I didn't want to be around
him anymore. -No. no. no. Stop.

1627
01:28:44.486 --> 01:28:46.362
- I want this gone!
- Okay.

1628
01:28:46.363 --> 01:28:49.073
I just want it gone!
I want it gone!

1629
01:28:49.074 --> 01:28:51.825
I want it gone! I just have
no mind of my own anymore!

1630
01:28:51.826 --> 01:28:53.994
Okay. stop! Stop!
Stop talking! Stop.

1631
01:28:53.995 --> 01:28:54.995
Give me your hands.

1632
01:28:54.996 --> 01:28:56.455
- Okay. look at me.
- No. no. no.

1633
01:28:56.456 --> 01:28:57.748
- Look at me.
- I-I'm gonna see things.

1634
01:28:57.749 --> 01:28:59.333
- I'm gonna see things. Please.
- Okay.

1635
01:28:59.334 --> 01:29:00.626
Breathe through your nose.
Breathe through your nose.

1636
01:29:00.627 --> 01:29:02.253
(both taking deep breaths)

1637
01:29:02.254 --> 01:29:04.004
That's it. Okay.

1638
01:29:04.005 --> 01:29:06.090
I can't feel my hands.

1639
01:29:06.091 --> 01:29:07.883
Okay. Okay.

1640
01:29:07.884 --> 01:29:09.510
Okay. give me your hands.
Come on.

1641
01:29:09.511 --> 01:29:11.512
- Come on. Put your hands there.
- (piano strings thrumming)

1642
01:29:11.513 --> 01:29:13.514
Feel that. Okay. you feel that?

1643
01:29:13.515 --> 01:29:15.266
I'm here. I'm here.

1644
01:29:15.267 --> 01:29:16.684
We're here.

1645
01:29:16.685 --> 01:29:18.520
- We're okay.
- Okay.

1646
01:29:19.479 --> 01:29:21.105
- We're okay.
- We're okay.

1647
01:29:21.106 --> 01:29:23.315
We're okay.

1648
01:29:23.316 --> 01:29:26.193
We're okay now. You're okay.

1649
01:29:26.194 --> 01:29:28.405
(heavy breathing continues)

1650
01:29:30.365 --> 01:29:32.491
We're okay.

1651
01:29:32.492 --> 01:29:34.034
Okay.

1652
01:29:34.035 --> 01:29:36.037
(breathing calms down)

1653
01:29:38.498 --> 01:29:40.542
Thank you.

1654
01:29:43.169 --> 01:29:45.713
Kellner called in from a gas
station outside Mount Leonard.

1655
01:29:45.714 --> 01:29:47.047
I'll meet Santiago and his crew.

1656
01:29:47.048 --> 01:29:49.384
We can be there
in a couple hours.

1657
01:29:50.260 --> 01:29:51.969
(Hugo grunts)

1658
01:29:51.970 --> 01:29:53.929
H-Hugo?

1659
01:29:53.930 --> 01:29:55.556
Could everyone leave
the staging area

1660
01:29:55.557 --> 01:29:56.932
for a minute. please?

1661
01:29:56.933 --> 01:30:00.102
- Now. please! Out!
- Yeah. Okay. let's go.

1662
01:30:00.103 --> 01:30:01.730
(sighs)

1663
01:30:04.149 --> 01:30:06.275
- (door opens)
- (groans)

1664
01:30:06.276 --> 01:30:07.986
SCANLON:
Hello. Hugo.

1665
01:30:09.154 --> 01:30:11.406
♪ ♪

1666
01:30:13.491 --> 01:30:15.619
Noah. please.

1667
01:30:16.411 --> 01:30:18.662
It's terribly misguided for you
to dive with that thing.

1668
01:30:18.663 --> 01:30:20.664
It's not a magic wand.

1669
01:30:20.665 --> 01:30:22.583
And it's not a weapon.
but it has functions

1670
01:30:22.584 --> 01:30:25.586
very far beyond
your limited use of it.

1671
01:30:25.587 --> 01:30:30.090
Kellner was an experiencer.
wasn't he?

1672
01:30:30.091 --> 01:30:32.259
That's why
I couldn't dive on him.

1673
01:30:32.260 --> 01:30:34.553
Yes.

1674
01:30:34.554 --> 01:30:36.598
He was.

1675
01:30:38.016 --> 01:30:42.479
And In Vivo 17
told you to recruit him?

1676
01:30:43.480 --> 01:30:45.439
Not in any way you'd understand.

1677
01:30:45.440 --> 01:30:46.982
If this is all their plan. Hugo.

1678
01:30:46.983 --> 01:30:49.693
you can be sure it's
in their interests. not ours.

1679
01:30:49.694 --> 01:30:52.279
That's a very lonely way
to look at the world.

1680
01:30:52.280 --> 01:30:53.697
No. don't condescend to me.

1681
01:30:53.698 --> 01:30:55.157
I'm listening to you. Noah.

1682
01:30:55.158 --> 01:30:57.451
Something I've learned
quite a bit about.

1683
01:30:57.452 --> 01:30:59.119
From your friends?

1684
01:30:59.120 --> 01:31:00.496
Yes.

1685
01:31:00.497 --> 01:31:03.624
They regard empathy
as an evolutionary advantage.

1686
01:31:03.625 --> 01:31:06.126
as the foremost
evolutionary advantage.

1687
01:31:06.127 --> 01:31:10.214
in fact. the core
of animate existence.

1688
01:31:10.215 --> 01:31:12.591
Our rejection
of this understanding

1689
01:31:12.592 --> 01:31:14.969
is leading us to our extinction.

1690
01:31:15.762 --> 01:31:18.973
And is your bleeding heart
why you helped it escape?

1691
01:31:20.767 --> 01:31:22.476
Five years ago.

1692
01:31:22.477 --> 01:31:24.646
That was you. wasn't it?

1693
01:31:26.189 --> 01:31:27.649
Yes.

1694
01:31:28.650 --> 01:31:31.610
The utter insanity
of that act aside.

1695
01:31:31.611 --> 01:31:33.862
how could you lie to me
for five years

1696
01:31:33.863 --> 01:31:35.489
every time you walked
through the door?

1697
01:31:35.490 --> 01:31:38.660
Everything you said to me.
it was all diversion.

1698
01:31:40.203 --> 01:31:43.664
When precisely did you lose
your bearings?

1699
01:31:43.665 --> 01:31:46.167
Around the time you lost yours.

1700
01:31:48.503 --> 01:31:50.171
When you lost her.

1701
01:31:54.259 --> 01:31:57.261
You lost her and almost
immediately were lost to me.

1702
01:31:57.262 --> 01:31:58.554
Because you shut down.

1703
01:31:58.555 --> 01:32:00.013
Do not presume to know me.

1704
01:32:00.014 --> 01:32:01.515
When she died.
you reduced everyone

1705
01:32:01.516 --> 01:32:03.267
to need-to-know. including me.

1706
01:32:03.268 --> 01:32:04.518
Because you were very clear.

1707
01:32:04.519 --> 01:32:05.894
All you needed to know was them.

1708
01:32:05.895 --> 01:32:08.355
and they are not knowable.
not by us.

1709
01:32:08.356 --> 01:32:10.899
They will be.

1710
01:32:10.900 --> 01:32:13.068
In Vivo 17 is nonhuman

1711
01:32:13.069 --> 01:32:14.945
but nearer to God. Noah.
than you or I.

1712
01:32:14.946 --> 01:32:17.115
You don't need to fear them.

1713
01:32:18.116 --> 01:32:19.950
I fear us.

1714
01:32:19.951 --> 01:32:23.078
The entire reason WARDEX exists
is because of our knowledge.

1715
01:32:23.079 --> 01:32:27.249
certain that the human race
cannot accept what we know.

1716
01:32:27.250 --> 01:32:29.334
That truth will upend
all established order

1717
01:32:29.335 --> 01:32:30.586
across the entire world.

1718
01:32:30.587 --> 01:32:33.088
The archive Kellner stole
is a virus

1719
01:32:33.089 --> 01:32:37.551
against which
the world has zero immunity.

1720
01:32:37.552 --> 01:32:39.928
I have spent 35 years
protecting...

1721
01:32:39.929 --> 01:32:41.263
Your own wealth and power--

1722
01:32:41.264 --> 01:32:43.307
that's all
you've been protecting.

1723
01:32:43.308 --> 01:32:46.059
Noah. Noah.

1724
01:32:46.060 --> 01:32:48.228
There is an essential need
in all of us to believe

1725
01:32:48.229 --> 01:32:51.732
and an equal need
to be believed.

1726
01:32:51.733 --> 01:32:53.942
You've violated
every standard of evidence.

1727
01:32:53.943 --> 01:32:55.569
You've infantilized anyone

1728
01:32:55.570 --> 01:32:58.322
who only wanted to understand
what they've witnessed.

1729
01:32:58.323 --> 01:33:01.241
You've brutally stifled
their questions.

1730
01:33:01.242 --> 01:33:04.036
shouted them down.
ridiculed and shamed

1731
01:33:04.037 --> 01:33:05.913
and overridden them
for the crime

1732
01:33:05.914 --> 01:33:08.040
of simply being astonished.

1733
01:33:08.041 --> 01:33:10.834
We believe the believers
and then deny the world

1734
01:33:10.835 --> 01:33:12.586
the chance to believe them. too.

1735
01:33:12.587 --> 01:33:15.297
But people keep wondering.
encountering the unknown.

1736
01:33:15.298 --> 01:33:17.090
telling others
of their experiences.

1737
01:33:17.091 --> 01:33:19.635
They are starved for the truth.

1738
01:33:19.636 --> 01:33:23.096
This 79-year terror campaign

1739
01:33:23.097 --> 01:33:26.809
of obfuscation. lies
and cover-up has to end!

1740
01:33:26.810 --> 01:33:28.769
We're ready to show you
a demonstration.

1741
01:33:28.770 --> 01:33:31.396
- HUGO: Get out! Get out!
- Sorry. sir. we have...

1742
01:33:31.397 --> 01:33:33.608
Turn around and get out now!

1743
01:33:38.571 --> 01:33:41.782
Pull up the 12 who didn't
show up to work yesterday.

1744
01:33:41.783 --> 01:33:44.785
I need faces
who are with him right now.

1745
01:33:44.786 --> 01:33:47.496
- Her.
- Grace Zhao. neuro-services.

1746
01:33:47.497 --> 01:33:49.248
- Him.
- Nathan Twinning.

1747
01:33:49.249 --> 01:33:50.499
Hugo's chief aide.

1748
01:33:50.500 --> 01:33:52.334
Got a back door
into their mobile providers.

1749
01:33:52.335 --> 01:33:54.128
Hang on.

1750
01:33:56.965 --> 01:34:01.761
They shut down their phones
last night... right here.

1751
01:34:02.804 --> 01:34:04.471
I'll project their routes ahead
to overlap.

1752
01:34:04.472 --> 01:34:07.558
I can give you the AI model
within a quarter-mile radius.

1753
01:34:07.559 --> 01:34:09.811
(Scanlon breathing heavily)

1754
01:34:13.690 --> 01:34:15.983
(church bell tolling
in distance)

1755
01:34:15.984 --> 01:34:18.820
Sister Maura. Sister.

1756
01:34:20.780 --> 01:34:22.991
(indistinct whispering)

1757
01:34:26.828 --> 01:34:28.453
Jane?

1758
01:34:28.454 --> 01:34:29.872
Where are you. Jane?

1759
01:34:29.873 --> 01:34:31.833
- (quiet chatter)
- (bell dinging)

1760
01:34:32.667 --> 01:34:34.209
Does God love us?

1761
01:34:34.210 --> 01:34:37.504
I don't mean. does he love us?
I know he does.

1762
01:34:37.505 --> 01:34:41.174
Does he love only us?

1763
01:34:41.175 --> 01:34:43.427
'Cause Genesis says that
we're his supreme creation.

1764
01:34:43.428 --> 01:34:46.471
but do you think
it's possible that...

1765
01:34:46.472 --> 01:34:48.016
SISTER MAURA:
On Earth.

1766
01:34:49.267 --> 01:34:50.517
What?

1767
01:34:50.518 --> 01:34:52.019
Genesis.

1768
01:34:52.020 --> 01:34:56.941
It says we are God's
supreme creation on Earth.

1769
01:34:58.526 --> 01:35:00.236
(bell dinging)

1770
01:35:05.825 --> 01:35:08.036
Do you think
there could be others?

1771
01:35:09.579 --> 01:35:11.705
Yes.

1772
01:35:11.706 --> 01:35:13.290
I would think so.

1773
01:35:13.291 --> 01:35:17.044
Why would he make
such a vast universe.

1774
01:35:17.045 --> 01:35:21.299
yet save it only for us?

1775
01:35:22.175 --> 01:35:27.346
If you found out
we weren't alone. if...

1776
01:35:27.347 --> 01:35:31.184
if someone showed you.
proved it to you...

1777
01:35:32.852 --> 01:35:35.145
...would that frighten you?

1778
01:35:35.146 --> 01:35:38.065
SISTER MAURA:
No. Why? Should it?

1779
01:35:38.066 --> 01:35:41.318
But what if it all collapsed?

1780
01:35:41.319 --> 01:35:43.904
For you and every other person
of faith in the world.

1781
01:35:43.905 --> 01:35:45.238
Then what?

1782
01:35:45.239 --> 01:35:46.448
Oh.

1783
01:35:46.449 --> 01:35:48.533
My dear. Jane.

1784
01:35:48.534 --> 01:35:53.580
I don't think that you ever
doubted your belief in God.

1785
01:35:53.581 --> 01:35:56.918
I think you lost your faith
in people.

1786
01:36:01.172 --> 01:36:04.926
They say you're paying because
you borrowed their phone?

1787
01:36:11.933 --> 01:36:13.767
Are you near the computer?

1788
01:36:13.768 --> 01:36:15.435
SISTER MAURA:
Yes.

1789
01:36:15.436 --> 01:36:17.771
What is KCXE?

1790
01:36:17.772 --> 01:36:20.441
Just those letters-- KCXE.

1791
01:36:27.699 --> 01:36:29.741
Remember being a kid?

1792
01:36:29.742 --> 01:36:31.159
Sure.

1793
01:36:31.160 --> 01:36:33.913
Mostly stuff after I was ten.

1794
01:36:38.626 --> 01:36:43.006
Can you tell anything about me
from when I was small?

1795
01:36:47.593 --> 01:36:49.804
♪ ♪

1796
01:37:01.816 --> 01:37:04.027
It's just a fox.

1797
01:37:10.783 --> 01:37:13.995
(brakes squealing)

1798
01:37:17.248 --> 01:37:18.957
DANIEL:
No. no. no. No!

1799
01:37:18.958 --> 01:37:21.877
- Stop! Stop!
- No. Daniel!

1800
01:37:21.878 --> 01:37:23.795
- (indistinct chatter)
- (grunting)

1801
01:37:23.796 --> 01:37:25.172
- Let's go. Come with us.
- Hold on.

1802
01:37:25.173 --> 01:37:27.507
- Hold on.
- Let's go.

1803
01:37:27.508 --> 01:37:29.134
I know him. I know him.

1804
01:37:29.135 --> 01:37:30.844
We just got to check you
real quick.

1805
01:37:30.845 --> 01:37:33.221
make sure nobody's in there
with you.

1806
01:37:33.222 --> 01:37:35.099
(electronic trilling)

1807
01:37:39.520 --> 01:37:40.687
(electronic trilling)

1808
01:37:40.688 --> 01:37:42.189
Clear.

1809
01:37:42.190 --> 01:37:44.357
All right. let's load up.

1810
01:37:44.358 --> 01:37:46.109
See. the thing about
fire trucks--

1811
01:37:46.110 --> 01:37:48.695
everyone gets the hell
out of your way.

1812
01:37:48.696 --> 01:37:50.948
♪ ♪

1813
01:38:04.754 --> 01:38:06.881
(Daniel inhales deeply)

1814
01:38:09.050 --> 01:38:11.302
♪ ♪

1815
01:38:37.161 --> 01:38:39.079
I knew you'd make it.

1816
01:38:39.080 --> 01:38:40.747
I'm glad you knew.

1817
01:38:40.748 --> 01:38:42.458
Never a doubt.

1818
01:38:49.590 --> 01:38:51.342
DANIEL:
Margaret.

1819
01:38:52.927 --> 01:38:54.470
Margaret.

1820
01:38:57.431 --> 01:38:58.933
Hello. Margaret.

1821
01:39:00.893 --> 01:39:03.145
Do you know who I am?

1822
01:39:03.146 --> 01:39:04.939
Of course. You're Hugo.

1823
01:39:07.608 --> 01:39:09.235
Nathan.

1824
01:39:10.528 --> 01:39:14.072
Chloe. Malik.

1825
01:39:14.073 --> 01:39:16.701
Jordan. Letisha.

1826
01:39:17.869 --> 01:39:19.786
Grace.

1827
01:39:19.787 --> 01:39:21.621
Hi. Terri.

1828
01:39:21.622 --> 01:39:23.541
Kaitlyn. That's Everett.

1829
01:39:33.634 --> 01:39:35.678
♪ ♪

1830
01:39:50.985 --> 01:39:53.321
I think we got it mostly right.

1831
01:39:54.739 --> 01:39:56.156
Margaret.

1832
01:39:56.157 --> 01:39:58.867
Why won't you look at me?

1833
01:39:58.868 --> 01:40:00.368
Because you're-you're the guy.

1834
01:40:00.369 --> 01:40:02.663
You're the guy
who knows everything.

1835
01:40:04.207 --> 01:40:07.251
And I'm... and I'm not ready
to know everything.

1836
01:40:08.669 --> 01:40:12.339
Including. like. why-why my mom
and dad's entire goddamn house

1837
01:40:12.340 --> 01:40:13.673
is just sitting right there!

1838
01:40:13.674 --> 01:40:16.968
What is going on?
Why are you doing this?

1839
01:40:16.969 --> 01:40:19.179
That's where I grew up.
That's where I grew up.

1840
01:40:19.180 --> 01:40:22.432
This is my life.
This is my life.

1841
01:40:22.433 --> 01:40:24.684
And this matters--
what I want. who I am.

1842
01:40:24.685 --> 01:40:28.564
not who I am as you
or him or her. but as me.

1843
01:40:32.526 --> 01:40:34.736
No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

1844
01:40:34.737 --> 01:40:37.114
No. No.

1845
01:40:38.366 --> 01:40:41.327
I will not be anyone's religion.

1846
01:40:49.001 --> 01:40:51.462
(sobbing)

1847
01:40:54.048 --> 01:40:56.259
♪ ♪

1848
01:41:06.560 --> 01:41:08.562
♪ ♪

1849
01:41:24.578 --> 01:41:26.706
(whimpers softly)

1850
01:41:51.856 --> 01:41:53.441
My room.

1851
01:41:57.111 --> 01:41:59.196
Oh. my room.

1852
01:42:25.973 --> 01:42:28.475
Why would you build all of this?

1853
01:42:28.476 --> 01:42:31.270
To create a passage.

1854
01:42:33.105 --> 01:42:35.190
To return you to your experience

1855
01:42:35.191 --> 01:42:38.151
in the most familiar way
possible.

1856
01:42:38.152 --> 01:42:40.571
What experience?

1857
01:42:42.531 --> 01:42:44.909
The one you shared
with Margaret.

1858
01:42:46.702 --> 01:42:47.952
I shared?

1859
01:42:47.953 --> 01:42:50.038
I am not going back there.

1860
01:42:50.039 --> 01:42:51.873
- Hugo. -How much do you
remember about that night?

1861
01:42:51.874 --> 01:42:53.750
I don't remember.
and I don't want to remember.

1862
01:42:53.751 --> 01:42:55.502
and I don't want you
making me remember.

1863
01:42:55.503 --> 01:42:57.879
- Okay. Oh. my...
- HUGO: Wait. Wait.

1864
01:42:57.880 --> 01:42:59.631
Wait.

1865
01:42:59.632 --> 01:43:01.591
Everything that happened to you
on the 23rd of February. 1996.

1866
01:43:01.592 --> 01:43:03.301
- is blocked. -I don't want
to know anything about it.

1867
01:43:03.302 --> 01:43:04.677
The only way for you
to know what's next

1868
01:43:04.678 --> 01:43:06.304
is to understand
what came before.

1869
01:43:06.305 --> 01:43:07.764
I don't want to talk about it.
I don't. Stop. stop. stop.

1870
01:43:07.765 --> 01:43:09.349
And then you'll know
your purpose.

1871
01:43:09.350 --> 01:43:10.600
Please don't make me.
I don't want to hear it.

1872
01:43:10.601 --> 01:43:11.518
You won't be
a passenger anymore.

1873
01:43:11.519 --> 01:43:13.604
I told you no! (gasps)

1874
01:43:18.234 --> 01:43:21.569
You have the gift
but no control.

1875
01:43:21.570 --> 01:43:23.696
No understanding
of your purpose.

1876
01:43:23.697 --> 01:43:25.490
Not a clue as to
what your situation

1877
01:43:25.491 --> 01:43:27.742
will demand of you beyond today.

1878
01:43:27.743 --> 01:43:30.370
The only way for you
to acquire it

1879
01:43:30.371 --> 01:43:33.998
is to go back
to where it all began.

1880
01:43:33.999 --> 01:43:35.709
To go home.

1881
01:43:41.590 --> 01:43:45.718
And when you do. Margaret.
you'll know everything.

1882
01:43:45.719 --> 01:43:49.306
More than what was ever
humanly possible.

1883
01:44:10.327 --> 01:44:12.579
They gifted each of you.

1884
01:44:12.580 --> 01:44:15.665
Margaret. what was dormant
in you for most of your life

1885
01:44:15.666 --> 01:44:18.627
was activated only yesterday.

1886
01:44:19.420 --> 01:44:22.005
And yours. 15 years ago.

1887
01:44:22.006 --> 01:44:24.090
They gave you fluency
in the language

1888
01:44:24.091 --> 01:44:26.843
in which the book
of the universe is written:

1889
01:44:26.844 --> 01:44:28.386
mathematics.

1890
01:44:28.387 --> 01:44:32.099
Taught it to you. imbued it
so you could understand them.

1891
01:44:32.933 --> 01:44:37.438
And they imbued you
so you could understand us.

1892
01:44:39.440 --> 01:44:42.066
It's the two of you.

1893
01:44:42.067 --> 01:44:43.485
(chuckles)

1894
01:44:43.486 --> 01:44:47.364
It's always been
just the two of you.

1895
01:44:55.623 --> 01:44:57.833
(quiet. indistinct chatter)

1896
01:45:09.386 --> 01:45:10.970
You can direct it

1897
01:45:10.971 --> 01:45:13.557
or feel where it wants
to take you.

1898
01:45:14.517 --> 01:45:16.601
It can find
what you're looking for.

1899
01:45:16.602 --> 01:45:19.604
It'll be an instrument
of your will.

1900
01:45:19.605 --> 01:45:22.149
But you must give yourself
over to it.

1901
01:45:23.150 --> 01:45:25.819
I'll find out
what's happening to me.

1902
01:45:28.197 --> 01:45:29.614
What?

1903
01:45:29.615 --> 01:45:31.324
It's gonna be okay.

1904
01:45:31.325 --> 01:45:32.952
I promise.

1905
01:45:40.084 --> 01:45:42.336
♪ ♪

1906
01:45:50.094 --> 01:45:51.678
Whatever happens. Daniel.

1907
01:45:51.679 --> 01:45:53.889
- don't you let go.
- Don't you let go.

1908
01:45:57.017 --> 01:45:58.644
Margaret.

1909
01:46:00.813 --> 01:46:03.107
Look around the room
one more time.

1910
01:46:04.525 --> 01:46:06.735
♪ ♪

1911
01:46:09.863 --> 01:46:13.533
You're a ten-year-old girl
asleep in your bed.

1912
01:46:13.534 --> 01:46:15.702
Something woke you up.
didn't it?

1913
01:46:15.703 --> 01:46:16.995
Yes.

1914
01:46:16.996 --> 01:46:18.747
So what did you do?

1915
01:46:19.540 --> 01:46:21.834
I sang my song.

1916
01:46:23.669 --> 01:46:26.880
(humming
"Someday My Prince Will Come")

1917
01:46:37.224 --> 01:46:40.977
♪ And away to his castle ♪

1918
01:46:40.978 --> 01:46:43.396
♪ We'll go ♪

1919
01:46:43.397 --> 01:46:47.233
♪ To be happy forever ♪

1920
01:46:47.234 --> 01:46:49.902
♪ I know ♪

1921
01:46:49.903 --> 01:46:54.074
♪ And the birds will sing. ♪

1922
01:47:00.039 --> 01:47:02.082
♪ ♪

1923
01:47:04.460 --> 01:47:07.086
I can see them.

1924
01:47:07.087 --> 01:47:09.047
Right over there.

1925
01:47:09.048 --> 01:47:11.050
They're coming into the room.

1926
01:47:13.469 --> 01:47:15.721
♪ ♪

1927
01:47:17.431 --> 01:47:20.643
(gruff. heavy breathing nearby)

1928
01:47:37.201 --> 01:47:38.661
(chitters softly)

1929
01:48:02.184 --> 01:48:04.228
♪ ♪

1930
01:48:06.980 --> 01:48:09.190
DANIEL:
No. no. no. don't go with them.

1931
01:48:09.191 --> 01:48:10.566
They're not animals.

1932
01:48:10.567 --> 01:48:12.652
Don't go with them.
They're not animals.

1933
01:48:12.653 --> 01:48:14.153
They're not animals!

1934
01:48:14.154 --> 01:48:15.988
- It's okay. It's okay.
- (panting) They're not.

1935
01:48:15.989 --> 01:48:20.035
They-they present as animals
to calm us.

1936
01:48:24.998 --> 01:48:27.834
When I walked through the glass.

1937
01:48:27.835 --> 01:48:32.005
it was like
this curtain of warm water.

1938
01:48:34.633 --> 01:48:37.260
And the snow...

1939
01:48:37.261 --> 01:48:40.681
was so warm on my feet.

1940
01:48:42.307 --> 01:48:45.268
(long. slow gasp)

1941
01:48:45.269 --> 01:48:47.229
The house.

1942
01:48:53.444 --> 01:48:56.113
"Hansel and Gretel."

1943
01:49:12.671 --> 01:49:14.882
(soft electrical warbling)

1944
01:49:21.221 --> 01:49:23.223
♪ ♪

1945
01:49:25.976 --> 01:49:28.228
(soft electrical warbling)

1946
01:49:31.398 --> 01:49:33.650
(soft whooshing)

1947
01:49:41.116 --> 01:49:42.867
(gruff. heavy breathing nearby)

1948
01:49:42.868 --> 01:49:45.746
(young Margaret
breathing heavily)

1949
01:49:58.133 --> 01:50:00.928
(chittering)

1950
01:50:11.522 --> 01:50:14.274
(rapid. gasping breaths)

1951
01:50:25.994 --> 01:50:27.746
Shh.

1952
01:50:33.418 --> 01:50:35.796
Hold my hand.

1953
01:50:44.346 --> 01:50:46.974
(young Daniel's breathing
slowing down)

1954
01:50:54.356 --> 01:50:56.400
♪ ♪

1955
01:50:59.319 --> 01:51:01.321
(trembling breaths)

1956
01:51:03.740 --> 01:51:06.034
- (soft electrical whooshing)
- (gasps)

1957
01:51:12.666 --> 01:51:14.918
(soft electrical crackling)

1958
01:51:27.848 --> 01:51:31.059
(soft whooshing. crackling)

1959
01:51:32.686 --> 01:51:34.938
- (sharp whoosh)
- (gasps)

1960
01:51:43.906 --> 01:51:46.158
♪ ♪

1961
01:51:48.827 --> 01:51:51.038
(soft whirring)

1962
01:51:54.499 --> 01:51:56.376
(soft whooshing)

1963
01:52:06.720 --> 01:52:08.972
(breathing heavily)

1964
01:52:12.392 --> 01:52:13.977
Whoa.

1965
01:52:15.729 --> 01:52:17.731
Whoa.

1966
01:52:34.331 --> 01:52:36.375
♪ ♪

1967
01:52:55.268 --> 01:52:57.104
Hello. Hugo.

1968
01:53:00.232 --> 01:53:02.776
It's so nice
to finally know you.

1969
01:53:03.610 --> 01:53:05.611
(tires squealing)

1970
01:53:05.612 --> 01:53:07.823
♪ ♪

1971
01:53:16.707 --> 01:53:18.959
(indistinct chatter)

1972
01:53:19.918 --> 01:53:21.711
They found us.

1973
01:53:21.712 --> 01:53:23.963
(labored breathing)

1974
01:53:23.964 --> 01:53:25.673
HUGO:
Are they out front or out back?

1975
01:53:25.674 --> 01:53:27.133
Most likely on all sides.

1976
01:53:27.134 --> 01:53:30.386
Okay. give me the. uh...
the-the-the thingy.

1977
01:53:30.387 --> 01:53:34.140
Thermal imaging showed
43 heat signatures inside here.

1978
01:53:34.141 --> 01:53:35.808
This whole area's
an industrial decay zone.

1979
01:53:35.809 --> 01:53:38.520
No other structure has
more than five people in it.

1980
01:53:40.022 --> 01:53:42.482
(heavy. labored breathing)

1981
01:53:45.986 --> 01:53:47.820
- (groans)
- Hey.

1982
01:53:47.821 --> 01:53:50.323
(grunts) Get on with it.

1983
01:53:54.911 --> 01:53:57.164
(whirring)

1984
01:54:06.631 --> 01:54:08.550
(electronic trilling. beeping)

1985
01:54:23.899 --> 01:54:26.151
♪ ♪

1986
01:54:34.576 --> 01:54:35.868
(hushed):
No one move.

1987
01:54:35.869 --> 01:54:38.162
No one make a sound.

1988
01:54:38.163 --> 01:54:39.915
They can't see us.

1989
01:54:43.126 --> 01:54:45.128
Give it to me.

1990
01:54:50.550 --> 01:54:52.344
This is not right.

1991
01:54:55.180 --> 01:54:59.101
They can't see us.
but they can see this.

1992
01:54:59.893 --> 01:55:02.561
We need to move now.

1993
01:55:02.562 --> 01:55:05.649
This is not gonna last long.
We got to go right now.

1994
01:55:15.909 --> 01:55:17.368
(hushed):
Look. They can't see me.

1995
01:55:17.369 --> 01:55:18.911
They can't see us. Let's go.

1996
01:55:18.912 --> 01:55:20.246
Quiet. quiet.

1997
01:55:20.247 --> 01:55:21.580
Through the back doors.
Any back door.

1998
01:55:21.581 --> 01:55:23.582
Go quiet. Go quiet.
Down the alley.

1999
01:55:23.583 --> 01:55:25.918
- Let's go. Let's go.
- Quiet.

2000
01:55:25.919 --> 01:55:28.879
Everybody. stop moving.

2001
01:55:28.880 --> 01:55:31.091
(rapid footsteps)

2002
01:55:36.888 --> 01:55:39.099
There. Look there.

2003
01:55:41.184 --> 01:55:43.018
Oh. God. I'm losing it.

2004
01:55:43.019 --> 01:55:44.645
I'm losing it.
You need to go faster.

2005
01:55:44.646 --> 01:55:46.480
- Get to the fire truck.
- I can't hold on.

2006
01:55:46.481 --> 01:55:47.940
- I can't hold...
- We got to go.

2007
01:55:47.941 --> 01:55:49.609
Stay on the light.

2008
01:55:52.696 --> 01:55:54.114
MARGARET:
I can't hold on.

2009
01:55:54.948 --> 01:55:57.325
- (groaning)
- (glass shattering)

2010
01:55:59.786 --> 01:56:00.953
- (loud thud)
- (groans)

2011
01:56:00.954 --> 01:56:02.204
(Margaret gasps)

2012
01:56:02.205 --> 01:56:04.123
- (creaking)
- (grunts)

2013
01:56:04.124 --> 01:56:05.791
DANIEL:
Let's go.

2014
01:56:05.792 --> 01:56:07.794
(device thrumming)

2015
01:56:08.628 --> 01:56:11.006
There. There.
Stay on the light.

2016
01:56:13.842 --> 01:56:16.469
- Stay on the light.
- The light! The light!

2017
01:56:18.763 --> 01:56:21.641
(groaning)

2018
01:56:26.980 --> 01:56:29.524
(groaning)

2019
01:56:34.196 --> 01:56:36.364
(engine starts)

2020
01:56:38.575 --> 01:56:40.492
(siren blaring)

2021
01:56:40.493 --> 01:56:42.495
(urgent chatter)

2022
01:56:43.663 --> 01:56:46.166
SANTIAGO: Hang on.
Grab ahold of something.

2023
01:56:49.836 --> 01:56:51.754
(frantic chatter)

2024
01:56:51.755 --> 01:56:53.923
(engine revving)

2025
01:56:53.924 --> 01:56:56.551
(siren blaring)

2026
01:56:58.053 --> 01:57:00.430
(second siren blaring)

